Commentary.Commentary: Now, The hosts will have to bat really well as it is not an easy pitch to bat on while India will look to make use of the new ball and take early wickets. Join us in a little while for the second session.

However, they were pretty solid yesterday when they picked up three early wickets but Rahane played a good innings of 81 runs and helped India make a comeback in the game. Jadeja along with Pant did well to see off the final session on Day 1. Jadeja then continued the good work in taking India's total closer to 300.

For the hosts, Roach was the pick of the bowlers as he picked up four wickets. As far as today is concerned, none of the bowlers looked threatening and gave away easy runs. They started well by getting Pant out early but lacked discipline after that.

With that wicket, it is LUNCH ON DAY 2. It has been India's day so far as they have added 94 runs in the session. Although the visitors lost Rishabh Pant early on in the day but Ishant Sharma and Jadeja put on a brilliant 60-run partnership to frustrate the hosts. Ishant finally fell when the score was 260 and Shami followed him soon after. Jadeja went on to counter-attack and reached his 11th fifty in the meantime. India have scored 297 runs which is a respectable total on this wicket.

OUT! Caught! Holder closes the Indian innings with his first wicket.  Lands this one on the shortish length which is coming on the body of Jadeja. He looks to slam this with a pull but gets a top edge as the ball hurries on to him. The ball goes high in the air behind the keeper as Shai Hope goes back to pouch that one comfortably. A fighting knock from Jadeja as he batted with the tail.
Good length ball on middle, Bumrah pushes it towards square leg to get Jadej on strike.
Good length ball on off, Bumrah defends it back to the bowler.
On a good length down the leg side, Bumrah looks to flick but misses.
Jason Holder comes into the attack.
Good length delivery outside the off stump line, Jadeja goes for a wild hoick but fails to put any bat on it.
Back of a length delivery on middle, RJ pushes this to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja defends it onto the ground to cover.
Short ball down the leg side, Jadeja leaves it alone.
On a good length on off, Jadeja drives this to mid off.
Shot! Bumrah drives this good length ball down the ground and they manage to take three and give Jadeja the strike.
Fuller one on middle, pushed straight to mid-wicket. No single there which means Bumrah will face Roach.
SIX! Heaved over mid-wicket  for a maximum. Tossed up one on middle, Jadeja gets in the position and smokes it over mid-wicket. He is getting into the groove now.

Short outside off again from Chase as Jadeja goes back and cuts it superbly to get a boundary. No chance for the fielder in the deep. Top shot to get to his half century, 11th in Tests. Brings out the sword celebration as well. He has battled for his runs here.
Shorter one  again, Jadeja pulls and refuses a single.
Shortish one on middle and off. Jadeja looked to pull this first but looking at the slowness of the ball, just tucked it towards square leg and scamper back for a couple. On 48 now.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja blocks it towards the off side.
And he does that with a solid defense coming forward.
Fuller one on the pads, Jadeja tucks it towards short mid-wicket and calls for a quick run. He wants the strike next over. One ball to survive for Bumrah.
Beaten on this outside off delivery which is on the good length area.
Fuller outside off, Jadeja pushes it towards cover and refuses a run.
FOUR! Slammed through covers. Fullish outside off for Jadeja. Enough room to power this through the cover to get a boundary. Nobody moved there.
Starts with a fullish delivery which is wide outside off, Jadeja lets it be.
Kemar Roach replaces Shannon Gabriel.
Plays the full toss straight back to the cover fielder. He sees of the over.
Looped up ball on middle this time, Bumrah blocks off his front foot.
Flighted ball on middle, Bumrah works it towards leg slip.
Fullish one this time, Bumrah comes forward to block.
Goes back to the crease to block this loopy ball to the leg side.
Fullish one to Bumrah who lunges forward to block.
Shortish one on off, Jadeja gets an inside edge which just misses the stumps.
FOUR BYES! Wide outside off again. Jadeja looks to power this but misses. The ball falls short of Shai Hope who can't collect it cleanly and allows it to go between his legs. Frustrating for Windies.
FOUR! Deliberate shot from Jadeja that one. Good length ball outside off, room for Jadeja there. He throws the bat at it and gets it past third slip and gully.
Fuller on the pads, Jadeja goes for the flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Good length on the fourth stump line, Jadeja blocks it towards point.
Shortish one outside off, Jadeja pushes this towards cover.
Another one down the leg side, Bumrah leaves it alone.
Bowls a loopy delivery way down the leg side. Bumrah leaves it alone.
Flighted delivery on middle, Bumrah defends it out.
Loopy delivery on off, Bumrah blocks it out.
Jasprit Bumrah is the last man in for the visitors.

OUT! Caught! Back to back wickets for West Indies. Soft dismissal this one. Loopy delivery on middle, Shami chips this towards the bowler who goes towards his right to pouch it comfortably. He went with a slightly harder hand to the ball but it goes off the inner half of the willow.
Fuller one outside off, Jadeja pushes this towards mid off to take a run.
Mohammad Shami joins Ravindra Jadeja in the middle.

OUT! Bowled him! West Indies have finally broken the stand. Gabriel goes for another fuller one outside off, rolled his fingers on that one. Ishant came forward to block this but gets an inside edge on to the Stumps. He looked solid out there. Chance for the Windies bowlers to wrap the innings before Lunch. Ishant's vital innings comes to an end.
Fuller this time to Ishant who walks across the off stump and flicks it nicely but finds the square leg fielder.
FOUR BYES! Poor line from Gabriel. Goes for the bumper but he is way down the leg side. The ball shapes further away from the diving keeper and rolls towards the fine leg fence. Important runs these.
Shortish one outside off, Jadeja pushes it towards point and calls for a quick run.
On the pads on a good length, Jadeja pushes it towards square leg to take a couple.

Nearly chopped on! Good length ball outside off, Jadeja looks to defend but the ball hits the inner half of the bat and drops near the stumps. Could've easily went on to hit the timber but bounces over.
Another one blocked coming forward by Ishant.
Good length on off, Ishant lunges to keep it out.
Fuller outside off, Ishant blocks it well.

Full toss on the pads of Ishant who does well to flick it through square leg. Gabriel there shows some foot work to stop a couple. Ishant got the bat in time or else he would've yorked himself in front of the stumps.
Fuller down the leg side. Sharma mises his flick on that one.
Goes fuller outside off, Jadeja pushes this through mid off to take a run.
Roston Chase is on now!
Another full delivery outside the off stump line, Ishant looks to defend but fails to put bat on it. There is a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire.
Goes for a full delivery outside the off stump, Sharma looks to defend but misses.
BOUNCER! It is bowled way above the head of the batsman. Ishant ducks under it.
Back of a length delivery on off, it goes off the splice of the bat towards short leg but falls well short.
Full delivery outside the off stump line, Ishant leaves it alone this time.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside the off stump line, Ishant goes for a drive but fails to get any bat on it.
Gabriel back on! His numbers so far, 19-4-64-2.
Good length outside off, Jadeja is not bothered.
Fuller on the pads of Jadeja who flicks it towards square leg and takes a quick couple to bring the 50-run stand. Vital runs added by these two as frustration grows for the Windies.
Another one outside off on the fifth stump line, Jadeja lets it be.
Outside off again, left alone again.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms. The ball shapes in after going past the batsman.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja blocks it towards the gully fielder.
Short delivery aimed at the body, Jadeja goes for the pull but hits it uppishly. It just bounced ahead of the square leg fielder. The batters take a single.
Back of a length delivery on middle, RJ defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja blocks it out.
OHH! On a good length ball on off, Ishant looks to flick but gets a thick outside edge towards square leg. It lands in between the two fielders and the batters take a single.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery! It is a good length ball outside off swinging away. Sharma goes for the defense but misses.
On a good length way outside off, Ishant leaves it alone.
Fuller down the leg side from Roach, Jadeja looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle,  Ishant works it fine down the leg side to take a run.

Huge appeal from Roach and Windies but nothing from the umpire. Good length ball outside off, Ishant looks to defend but he is hit high on the pads. Roach goes for a huge appeal but nothing from the umpire. Good decision from Holder to not go for the review as the impact was outside off shown by the Ball Tracker.
Fuller outside off, Ishant guides it towards the slip cordon.
Fullish one on the pads of Ishant. He works it nicely towards mid-wicket to take a couple.
Beaten! Good length ball outside off from Roach. Ishant wants to drive this one but the ball shapes away a bit goes past the outside edge. New ball is troubling Ishant here.
Good length ball on middle and off, comes slightly into him who blocks it well.
Bumper again but down the leg side. Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Another bouncer but this time on the body. Ishant comfortably works it towards square leg to take a run. 250 up for India. Frustrating stand this one as long as Windies are concerned.
Short and wide outside off, Ishant lets it go.
Shortish delivery outside off this time, Ishant pats it towards gully.
Back of a length ball coming in to the body of Ishant who hops to block it towards the leg side but is late and he is hit on the body.
The physio is out there to have a check on Jadeja who is having some issues with his right hand. He seems fine and is ready to continue the battle.
Fuller on off, Jadeja blocks it well towards off side.
FOUR! Crunched! Goes for a bumper on the body but this doesn't rise much. Perfect height for Jadeja to swivel and slams this deep down the leg side to get a boundary.
Outside off on a good length, Jadeja pushes it towards cover to take a run.
This time he is behind the line of the ball as he pats it towards the off side to change ends.
Beaten this time! Short ball outside off, Ishant looks to defend but he is beaten as the ball shapes away.
Back of a length on the body of Jadeja who works it towards square leg to take a run.

DRINKS! It has been India's hour. West Indies, after taking the early wicket of Rishabh Pant, have struggled to take a wicket thereon. Jadeja and Ishant are in the middle of a good partnership and have taken India close to 250. Kemar Roach will bowl after the break.
Good length ball on off, Sharma pushes this towards point.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.

Edged but just short! Why didn't Shai Hope go for the catch there? Good length ball which shapes away from Ishant and takes the outside edge of the bat. It goes towards the first slip fielder but was closer to the keeper who could've swallowed that with a dive to his right.
Short on the body this time, Jadeja pulls this towards mid-wicket to take a run.
The second new ball has been taken by the hosts.
Bowls a full delivery on middle this time, Jadeja blocks it well.
FOUR! Punched nicely. Short ball outside off, enough room for Jadeja to slam this between point and gully. The ball races towards the fence. It evades the diving fielder from deep point.
Fuller outside off, Ishant taps it towards point.
Shortish on the body this time for Ishant who tucks it towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Back of length outside off, Ishant looks to poke at this away going ball but he is beaten as he plays down the wrong line.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja taps it towards cover and takes a run.
Shortish on middle this time, Ishant works it down the leg side to take a single.

Good length ball on off this time, Jadeja comes forward to block but the ball goes off the inner half of his bat to hit the pad and roll down the leg side. Jadeja crosses ends. India have scored their first run after three overs.
Good length ball outside off, Ishant blocks this one well.
Gets this one to shape away from the right-hander from the good length angle. Ishant pokes at it and is beaten.
Bouncer down the leg side as Ishant misses his flick. The ball shapes away from Shai Hope who does well to pouch that.
Good length ball on middle this time, Ishant blocks it well.
Another good length ball outside off, Ishant covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper as he sees the ball shape in.
Good length around off, Ishant blocks it well towards the off side.
Shortish one closer to the body, Jadeja taps it close to his body.
Full ball outside off on the fifth stump line, Jadeja lets it go once again.
Bowls a full one this time, Jadeja lets it go to the keeper again.
Shorter in length this time on off, the ball goes further away, Jadeja is  not bothered and lets it go.
Full delivery outside off, Jadeja lets it be.
Fullish one outside off to start the new over, Jadeja times it straight to cover.
BOUNCER! Holder bowls this one down the leg side and Ishant lets it go to the keeper.
Another good length ball outside off, Ishant does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
BEATEN! On a good length outside off, Ishant looks to defend but just misses the edge of the bat.
Full delivery on off, Ishant drives this to cover.

LEG BYE! Good length ball on off, Jadeja looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. Holder makes a stifled appeal but nothing from the umpire. The replays show that the ball was missing the leg stump. Good decision not to go for the review.
On a good length outside off, Jadeja guides it to gully.
Jason Holder comes back on.
Good length outside off, Ishant defends this off his back foot.
Shortish outside off this time, Ishant walks across and has a push but is beaten.
Good length this time, Ishant times it straight to the cover fielder.
Shortish one again outside off, Ishant pushes it off his back foot towards the off side.
Slightly shortish on off, Ishant looks to defend but gets an inside edge and the ball hits him on the pads.
Good length on middle and leg, Jadeja tucks it towards the leg side to take a run.
First bowling change of the morning. Miguel Cummins comes into the attack.
FOUR! Nicely played! Goes for a yorker but ends up as a low full toss. Ishant brings his bat down in time to squeeze this between third slip and gully. Nicely done. Another 7-run over for India.
On the pads again from Gabriel on a fuller length, Jadeja works it towards mid-wicket to take a run.
Down the leg side again on a good length. Jadeja lets it go to the keeper.
Fullish on off, Jadeja pushes this towards cover and calls for a quick couple. Good running that from him.
Bumper down the leg side from Gabriel. Jadeja lets it go.
Shortish one on middle, Jadeja plays it towards point.
Looks for a yorker but dishes out a full toss, Ishant does well to flick it towards mid-wicket to take a couple. 7 runs from the over.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja pushes this towards mid off this time.
Good length on off and middle, Ishant taps it onto the pitch to the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Ishant pushes this towards mid on.
Good length outside off, Jadeja works it towards cover to take a run.

FOUR! Fullish ball outside off, Jadeja leans forward and directs the ball through the backward point fielder. The ball races to the fence as the fielder chases. However, the ball wins the race. First boundary of the day.
Shorter one this time, Ishant goes on his toes and dabs it towards leg slip.
Good length on middle and off, Sharma tucks it towards square leg to take a couple.
Fullish outside off for Jadeja who drives it sweetly past the mid off fielder. Again, the slowish outfield means it won't reach the fence. The batters take three.

Fullish length ball but this is down the leg side, Jadeja looks to tickle it fine down the leg side but the ball hits him on the pads and races towards the fence. However, Roach comes from deep fine leg to stop the ball. Two runs taken.
Good length ball on middle, coming in to the batsman, Jadeja pats it back to the bowler.
Fullish on the fourth stump. Jadeja blocks it well.
Fullish ball on the fifth stump line, kept slightly low as Ishant looks to poke. He is beaten.
Shortish on middle this time, coming into the body of Jadeja who works it fine down the leg side to take a run.
Good length on the fifth stump line this time, Jadeja lets it be.
Good length on the fourth stump line, Jadeja taps it back to the bowler.
Goes for a bumper but this is just hip height on middle, Ishant works it towards mid-wicket to take a run.
Fuller one to Ishant first up who blocks it straight to cover.
Another good length delivery outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone. This means Ishant will be on strike for the next over.
NO BALL! Shannon Gabriel oversteps here. It is a good length ball outside the off stump line, RJ leaves it alone.
Short delivery which is bowled down the leg side, Jadeja does not fiddle with it and lets it go.
On a good length outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Another shortish one on the body, this time to Ishant who hops to work it towards square leg to take a run. He's off the mark.
Short on the body again, Jadeja looks to pull this one but doesn't time it well. The ball goes towards square leg and Jadeja crosses ends.
Good leave! Gabriel is bowling well here. Shortish on middle and leg going away. Jadeja sways away from it.
Good length ball on off, Sharma blocks it well off his front foot.
Ishant Sharma is the next batsman in.

OUT! Caught! West Indies strike early. Number four for Roach. Good length ball closer to the fourth stump. Pant after hitting a couple of good shots goes hard at the ball. It shapes a tad bit away to take an outside edge and go to the Windies skipper, Holder who takes it comfortably at second slip. One would wonder if this style works for Pant as he looked to get in. Maybe he should play with the attacking instinct that he possesses. For now, West Indies have the upper hand now as he could've been dangerous. The question which stands is how Jadeja will play from here?
Fullish outside off this time, Pant leans into the drive to time it superbly through the covers. The outfield is slow and the ball doesn't reach the fence. Two runs taken.
Good length ball shaping away from the batter, Pant is not going to do anything on that.
Good length on middle, Pant blocks it towards the leg side.

Fuller one outside off, Pant leans to drive this past the diving cover fielder who gets his hands to it and slows the ball down. They take a couple before the ball is relayed back to the keeper. First runs off the day.
Kemar Roach comes into the attack.
Fullish one outside off, Jadeja pats it towards point and looks for a run but is sent back.
Shortish on middle again on the body. Jadeja hops but gets hit on the gloves.
Good length ball on middle, goes down the leg side as Jadeja misses his flick.
Ripper this time! Another shortish one on middle, going away from Jadeja who looks to fend at the ball. Lucky that the ball didn't kiss the bat or glove.
Shortish one on middle, angling away from Jadeja who looks to cut this one through point and cover. Misses his slash.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Shannon Gabriel will start the proceedings from the other end.
Starts with a shortish one on middle, Pant taps it to point.
Finally, the West Indian players make their way out to the middle along with the overnight batsmen, Jadeja and Pant. Roston Chase will finish his over with Pant taking strike. Here we go...

We should've been underway by now as per the information given at Stumps on Day 1 but we are yet to begin. Seems like we will have an extended final session which means we will be starting at normal time, 0930 local. If there is any further information, will keep you updated.

The first day of this Test ended early as rain took centre stage and as a result the play will begin half an hour earlier today (Local 0900). The visitors will be having mixed emotions following the play on Day 1 as they recovered from a bad start to end the day on 203/6. Looking forward to today's play, India will be looking to get to the 300-run mark which will be an above par score on this pitch. As for the Calypso Kings, they will try to bowl out the Men In Blue before they reach 250. Join us in a while as an important first session awaits us on Day 2.

Greetings and a warm welcome to our coverage of Day 2 of the Test match between West Indies and India. We have positive news in terms of  the weather as the sun is shining and the chances of showers are minimal.
... Day 2, Session 1 ...

Now, what will be on offer for Day 2? This is the last recognized batting pair for the Indians. The two left-handers can go bonkers from ball one and add quick runs for the Indians to take them towards a strong total. Or, bat long and hard, tire out the home side and take the total close to 300 without being separated. West Indies will look to get rid of this pair and then look to get through the tail. Also, we will be starting 30 minutes from the routine time to cover the lost overs of Thursday. Join us on Friday, 23rd August, 2019 at 9 am local (1300 GMT). Till then, goodbye!

The Windies opening bowlers, Roach and Gabriel returned to thump the Indians with two quick wickets as they removed Vihari and Rahane. Pant and Jadeja were looking decent in the middle when rain arrived to cut the day short.

West Indies were on top early on, courtesy brilliant spells from Roach and Gabriel. It looked like going towards their way but KL Rahul and Ajinkya Rahane stitched a superb 68-run stand to pull the things back towards the visitors. A fluent-looking Rahul failed to convert his start yet again, getting a soft dismissal down the leg side but Rahane continued the good work for the side. He, along with Hanuma Vihari, added 82 runs, raking up his half ton in the process, to take things slightly away from the Windies.

End of an exciting day's play then. The Indians have done well after early hiccups to reach 203 in 68.5 overs. Very difficult to say who holds an edge after Stumps but this is heading towards an exciting Day 2.
Done and dusted for the day then as rain becomes heavier. The umpires were doing an inspection when the rain became heavier. They decide that we won't be able to return and that will be Stumps.

Update 1650 Local (1250 GMT) -  Scratch what we just said. It has started to rain again and the umpires are out in the middle with their umbrellas open. It's raining heavily right now and maybe that should be end of the day's play.

Update 1645 Local (1245 GMT) - It seems like the rains are playing hide and seek with us as it has stopped to rain now. The covers are coming off and the play should resume shortly. The umpires are out in the middle doing the inspection of the pitch.

Ha ha ha! Who knows the ground and the weather better than the local groundsmen. They sensed that the rain was around and started pulling the covers. However, the umpires asked them to return back. And, as they were going back, it started bucketing down and the umpires had to call them back. That means another rain stoppage as the players walk into the pavilion.
Outside off again, Pant lets it go by covering his stumps.
Fuller again to Pant, times it straight to mid off
On middle and leg, defended back to the bowler.
Shortish outside off, Pant pushes it towards point.
Fullish outside off, no turn on that one. Pant lets it go to the keeper.

Looks like the groundsmen will be coming onto the pitch as rain looks imminent. Dark clouds can be seen coming from afar and the ground staff is looking ready for any stoppage. It is looking very very windy as the covers are not even staying on the ground.
Slightly fullish outside off, Jadeja lets it be.
Good length on off and middle this time, Jadeja pushes this towards point.
Jadeja lunges to block this good length ball off.
Good length on middle and off, blocked well by RJ.
Fuller this time, came in to Jadeja who was late to bring his bat down. But lucky that got a thick part of the bat to block it.
Shortish one coming into the batsman, Jadeja taps this off his back foot towards point.
Fuller one again as Pant blocks towards cover.
Fullish from Chase this time on middle, Jadeja works towards long on to cross ends.
Lunges to this fuller ball again to block well.
Good length on middle and off, blocked off his front foot.
Comes forward to this good length ball to dab it towards point.
Turned away from Jadeja that one. Good length outside off, Jadeja looks to work it towards off side but misses.
On the fifth stump line outside off, Pant lets it go to the keeper again.
Another one outside off on a good length, Pant lets it be.
Good length on middle this time from Holder, tapped back to the bowler.
Good length outside off, left alone by Pant.
Beauty to get past the bat! Shortish one, angled into the left-hander. Pant looks to fend at it off his toes but this shoots off the surface. Lucky was Pant there as the ball didn't kiss his gloves.
Shortish outside off, asking Pant to throw the kitchen sink at the ball. Pant leaves it alone.
Good length on off, Jadeja blocks it well.
Fuller on which is worked towards mid off.
Fuller on the legs, blocked towards the leg side.
Full ball again on middle, pushed towards mid off for a run.
FOUR! Shot! Another full ball on middle, this time to Pant who slams this over the cover region to get a boundary. Top shot that one which brings the 200 up for India as well.

In the air but safe! Fuller ball on middle as Jadeja looks to lift this over the cover fielder. He gets a leading edge to that as the ball lobbed in the air towards cover. Nobody there and the batters take one.
Roston Chase is back into the attack now. 9-1-36-1 so far from him.

DRINKS!   Good initial hour for the Windies in this final session as they have removed set Rahane and Vihari. Rahane looked well set for his ton but got out very unfortunately. Pant has played a couple of top shots but have beaten on a couple of balls as well. With him and Jadeja in the middle, one would expect the runs to be flowing. Interesting to see if the Windies can get rid of the last recognized batting pair to into the Indian tail.

Definitely a chance for three but the batters take just two. Pant drives this fuller one outside off towards the gap at covers. The ball does not have enough power on it to cross the fence. Shannon Gabriel gives it a tired chase and cuts it off a couple of yards inside the fence. Pant was halfway down the pitch but Jadeja sends him back as he didn't want the third.
Full ball outside off, pushed to mid off.
Fuller again but much straighter, pushed to mid on by Rishabh.
Fullish ball outside off, Pant drives this one towards the mid off fielder.
FOUR! Beautiful drive and the ball just trudges towards the fence. Good length ball outside off, Pant leans into the cover drive and finds the gap as the ball races to the fence.
Outside off, left alone by Pant.
Jason Holder back on!
Length ball on off pole, RJ blocks it out.
Full outside off, pushed to the fielder at cover.
Fuller this time on the off pole, Jadeja pushes this straight past the bowler but the fielder at mid on cuts it off.
On a length outside off, Jadeja lets it be.
Again outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to it.
Way outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Wide outside off, left alone by Pant.
Short one outside off, Pant looked to pull initially but stopped to drop it off his back foot onto the pitch.
This time Pant middles his flick to this fullish ball but finds the square leg fielder.

Huge appeal now! Fullish ball on middle and leg from Gabriel and Pant misses his flick. Gabriel appeals for an LBW but that looked like pitching outside leg. Holder thinks for a review but decides against it. Good call in the end from the Windies skipper that as Ball Tracker confirmed that it was pitched outside leg.
Fuller outside off, left alone by Pant.
Good length outisde off from Gabriel, Pant has a poke at it only to get an outside edge towards third slip but the ball falls just shot of him.

NOT OUT! Jadeja knew he had edged it and that's why he had straight away gone for the review. Length ball just outside off, it pitched and came back in with the angle. Jadeja looked to hit it towards the off side but it seemed that he missed the ball. The Windies team went all out in appealing and the umpire raised the finger after thinking about it for a while. Jadeja straightaway went for the review. Replays roll in, Hawk Eye comes into play and shows that yes, Jadeja's judgement was right. He did get an inside edge on it before the ball hit the pad.

Jadeja has been given out LBW after a loud appeal but Jadeja goes for the review instantly. He has got it right as well as he got an inside edge into the pads which is confirmed by the Ultra Edge. Decision overturned.
Blocks this fuller one outside off back to the bowler.
This time outside off but full, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Jadeja.
Jadeja has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full ball outside off, pushed to the fielder at cover.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
On the pads, Jadeja flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single to get off the mark.
Ravindra Jadeja walks out to the middle. Will we see a sword celebration from him? India needs runs from him here.

OUT! Bowled! Chopped on! Rahane is dismissed on 81 and one must say it is a very soft dismissal after a great innings so far. Length ball outside off, Gabriel bowls this one coming in with the angle. Rahane looks to cut it but gets an inside edge on it and the ball is chopped onto the leg stump. Rahane looks distraught at how he has got out and one can say he has rode his luck in this innings. Rahane departs and India are 6 down for 189 with two new batters are at the crease. Window of opportunity for the hosts?
Good length delivery on the off pole, blocked out.
Wide outside off, left alone by Ajinkya.
Full ball on middle and leg, pushed to mid on by AR.
Rahane plays this full ball towards the covers and takes a quick single.
Good length ball and defended off the front foot by Rahane.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Full and on the pads of Rahane, he flicks it towards deep square leg and takes a quick couple.  The fielder from the deep does throw it quickly towards the keeper's end but Rahane is well in by the time Hope removes the bails.
Rahane presents the full face of the bat and defends it towards the off side.
Good length ball on the off pole, Rahane blocks this one towards the off side.
Bouncer down the leg side, Pant ducks and leaves it alone.
Length ball on middle and leg, the batter pushes it towards mid on.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Pant defends it towards mid on.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Pant goes onto the back foot and cuts it through point for a boundary. He looks in good touch here. Second boundary from Pant in this innings.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery. The ball goes towards mid on.
Length ball just outside off, Pant looks to play the cover drive but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball goes towards gully off the edge. No runs taken.
Full and around off, Pant pushes it towards mid on and takes a single.

Left alone but mightily close to the stumps as the ball swings in. The ball pitches on a good length outside off, it swings in and goes past the stumps. Pant must be pretty sure of where his wickets are.
Full and around off, pushed to covers.
Outside off, left alone by Pant.
Length ball on middle and off, Rahane guides this towards deep point and takes a single as Hetmyer cuts it off running to his left.
Good length ball on the off side, Rahane blocks it out.

FOUR! Low full toss on the pads and given the right treatment by Pant. He just flicks it towards the gap at mid-wicket and the ball races towards the fence. First boundary for Pant and he is off the mark with this.
Good length ball on the off side, Pant blocks this towards the cover fielder.
Short of a length ball outside off, the ball shoots off the pitch and moves away too. Pant tries to put bat on it but misses. Luckily!
On the pads again, Rahane nudges it towards deep fine leg and takes a single.
Down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it towards the off side.
Oh! No slash there from Pant to this wide outside off delivery. How long will he be reluctant?
Rishabh Pant arrives! How will he start his innings? Aggression? Calmness? Plenty to look forward to as he walks out in the middle.

OUT! CAUGHT! The West Indies have again found a breakthrough at a crucial moment and half the Indian side is back in the hut. Roach bowls this one on a length, on the fourth stump line. He gets this one to swing away after pitching. The edge is induced from Vihari and the ball barely carries to Hope but he dives well in front to take a low catch. Vihari will be disappointed to get a good start and then depart at such a crucial time. Third wicket for Roach in this innings.
Way wide outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Vihari guides it towards third slip on the bounce with soft hands.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari blocks it out.
Full and on the pads, Rahane pushes this towards mid-wicket and takes a single.
Short and wide again, Rahane cuts it towards deep point for a single.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.

Beaten and a appeal out of desperation by the Windies for caught behind. Rahane slashes at this short and wide delivery but he misses. Gabriel appeals but even he knows there is not much in it. Ultra Edge confirms that no edge is on that delivery.
Length ball on middle, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Outside off, left alone by Rahane.

Awkward bounce here off the pitch. The ball is pitched on a good length and goes between the bat and pad of Vihari as he looks to push it towards the off side. It rises rapidly on keeper Hope and he fails to collect it. The ball hits his glove and rolls towards fine leg as they take a single.
Gabriel is on as well from the other end. His numbers till now - 10-2-38-1
Beaten! Good length ball just outside off, Rahane is beaten this time as the ball swings away this time. It beats the outside edge of Rahane's bat and into the gloves of the keeper.
FOUR! Cut and to the fence. Short and wide outside off, Rahane pounces on it as he goes onto the back foot and cuts it through point.
Length ball on the off pole, Ajinkya blocks this one out towards the off side.
Fuller on the pads, Rahane pushes this towards mid-wicket.
On a length just outside off, Rahane blocks this one out.
Outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Kemar Roach replaces Chase.
Defended off the back foot by Vihari.
FOUR! Great shot by Vihari. He pushes this full one powerfully through mid on and to the fence for a boundary.
Edged but well short! Outside off as Vihari fends at from the crease, played with soft hands and that's why it went to the slip fielder on the bounce.

Fuller outside the off pole, Rahane whips this towards mid-wicket and sets off. The ball is slowly trudging towards the fence but Holder from mid-wicket gives it a chase and keeps it inside the field as the batters take three.
Another one on similar line and length. Rahane blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane blocks it out.
Shortish one outside off, Rahane pushes this towards cover to take a run.
Fuller one this time, drives it towards mid on to take a run.
Gives this a bit of air, Vihari blocks it well.
Flighted on middle, pushes straight to the fielder.
Fullish one on off, drives it towards mid on to take a run.

FOUR! Short and wide outside off. Enough time for Rahane to go back and slam this through cover-point to get a boundary. The fielder races to stop this with his footwork, but the ball tickles to kiss the ropes.
This one coming in to the batsman, worked it towards mid-wicket.
Blocks this from within the crease to this good length ball.
EDGED and FOUR! Short ball outside off, Vihari lures at it and goes for the cut over the point fieldsman but the ball gets an outside edge and flies over the right of first slip.
Beaten this time. Length ball just outside off, the ball pitches and straightens. Vihari looks to defend but is squared up.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Hanuma tries to block it out but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball goes in the gap between gully and the slip cordon towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Fuller outside off, Vihari blocks it out towards the off side.
Goes back to this shortish ball and dabs it towards the leg side.
Blocked this time off his back foot.
Full ball on middle, blocked by Rahane.

FOUR! Loosner down the leg side, Rahane pulls this one between the wicket-keeper and the short fine leg fielder to another boundary. 50-run stand between the two. India needed  to steady the ship after the wicket of KL Rahul and the duo have done their job brilliantly.
Another fullish ball on middle, Rahane walks across and whips this towards mid-wicket to take another couple.
Fullish ball on middle, Rahane dabs it towards short leg who is alert to stop
Roston Chase to bowl from the other end for the hosts.
Good length outside off, Vihari dabs it well towards point off his back foot.
Full ball on leg, Rahane times it towards the right of the mid-wicket. Times it well but the wetness of the surface meant that the ball doesn't have legs to go to the fence. 3 runs taken.
Short one again as Rahane swivels to pull this towards square leg to take a couple.
Short ball on the body to start after the rain delay. Vihari looks to work it on the leg side but the ball rises a bit.  The batsman does well to drop it fine to take a run.

The rain has stopped, the covers are off the pitch and we are all set to begin. The sun is shining and the dark clouds have gone away. The hosts are out on the field. Hanuma Vihari and Ajinkya Rahane are also on the pitch with the former taking the strike. Miguel Cummins will resume proceedings for the Calypso Kings post Tea. Vihari on strike...
... Day 1, Session 3 ...
Update 1440 local (1840 GMT) - We have an update after that inspection. We will begin the final session at 1455 local, weather permitting.

Update 1433 local (1833 GMT) - Well, the tea time is over but seems we will have a slightly delayed start for the final session of the day. No rain there but the covers are on the pitch. Also, we have the umpires doing the inspection. Shouldn't be long before we start.

So, the heavens have opened up and the umpires have declared for early Tea to be taken. The visitors are 134/4 and have just lost one wicket of KL Rahul in this session. He will be pretty disappointed in the manner in which it happened though as he was looking set for a big score. Ajinkya Rahane survived two scares before he reached his half ton as he was dropped on alternate balls by Miguel Cummins and Shai Hope respectively. After KL's departure, Vihari walked in and looked pretty solid out in the middle adding a 41-run stand with Ajinkya Rahane. Do come back and join us as we resume the third session on Day 1.
Covers coming on! Where did that came from. Smart from the umpires as they call for covers seeing the heavy wind. Also, they have taken an early Tea.
Shortish on off again from Cummins, plays off his back foot.
Shortish one off to start, Vihari pushes this back to the bowler.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends this length ball off the back foot towards the off side.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
A little confusion but no harm done. Rahane pushes this one towards point. Vihari wants one but is sent back by Rahane.
Tossed up on the pads, Vihari tucks it towards square leg for one.
Floated on middle, Vihari whips it towards deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Rahane blocks it out.

FIFTY for Rahane, his 18th in Tests. Fullish ball outside off, Rahane leans and creams this through the cover region to get a couple. He has been off color in Tests for a while but he has stood up here for the side. A top knock from him.
Good timing but straight to the mid on. Full ball from Cummins on off to which Rahane leans forward and times it sweetly. No run off a very good shot.
Good length ball on fourth stump line, Rahane dabs this off his back foot.
Shortish one outside off, Rahane lets it go.
Shortish one outside off, came in to Rahane. He works it off his back foot towards point.
Way short and on the body, Vihari looks to pull but it hits the top half of his bat and the ball falls on the leg side.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
The batsman dances down the track but decides to defend it.

Good running now by the batters. Vihari pushes this shorter one towards third man, he quickly completes the first and goes the second as well. They complete two comfortably because of the slowness of the Windies players to react to the situation.

FOUR! The sweep shot used to great effect here by Hanuma. He looks in good touch. Floated on middle and leg, Hanuma comes onto the front foot and sweeps this one towards fine leg where the fielder lets it go through his legs and the ball races to the fence.
Floated on leg, Vihari flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Vihari pushes this one towards cover with soft hands and takes a single.
On the pads of Vihari, he flicks it towards the leg side. Good reflexes by the man at short leg to save a run.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full ball on the off side, pushed through covers and the batters take a single as the man from mid off cuts it off.
This one shoots off the pitch. Bowled on a length on the body, the ball rises on Vihari. He gets a glove on it as the ball rolls towards square leg. The batters take one.
Length ball outside off by Cummins, Rahane pushes it towards point and take one.
Miguel Cummins replaces Holder. 5-0-18-0, his numbers so far.
Vihari goes for a wild  sweep but misses this leg sided delivery.
Floated on off and middle, Vihari blocks this one towards the leg side.
Flat on middle, Hanuma blocks it out.
Floated on the pads this time, Rahane flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
Flat and on middle, Rahane blocks it out.
Flat and down the leg side, Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Fullish on off, Vihari lunges to block towards mid off.
Wide outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Short outside off this time, Rahane swivels and pulls this to deep square leg to take a run.
That came in from the good length on off and middle, Vihari worked it nicely towards mid-wicket to get off strike.
Shortish one on middle, Vihari blocks it off his back foot, short leg fielder does well to stop that.
Shortish one this time, Rahane hops in his crease and works it towards the point fielder. Sets off for a quick single. Good running that.

DROPPED AGAIN! But it was a tough one. Chase floats this down the leg side on a good length for Rahane who looks to tickle it fine but the ball kisses his gloves and goes fine. Shai Hope gets a hand to it down the leg side but the ball just deflects enough for him to miss the catch. Rahane is riding is luck here and he might soon run out of it if he is not careful.
Fullish on middle, Rahane tucks it towards mid-wicket for no run.

DROPPED! Lucky lucky Ajinkya Rahane. This was tossed up and on middle and leg, Rahane comes down the track looking to go for the biggie over mid on. He gets a leading edge on it and the ball goes high and straight over the bowler's head. Cummins from mid on runs back, gives it a chase, reaches the ball and gets two hands on it but puts it down. He quickly throws the ball back towards Chase and the batters take two in the meantime. Lifeline given to Ajinkya.
Floated around off, Rahane blocks it out.
Short and just wide outside off, Rahane rocks back onto the back foot and cuts it through backward point for a double.
Flat outside off, Rahane blocks this one towards the bowler.
Bouncer again by Holder to end the over. He ducks and lets the ball through to Shai Hope.
Down the leg side, Vihari looks to flick but misses.
On the pads of Hanuma, he flicks it towards the fielder at square leg.
Wide outside off, Hanuma does not fiddle with it.
Another bouncer, Vihari again sways away from it.

Good bouncer by Holder, using his height well. This ball pitches short and well outside off, it comes back in more than Vihari expected. It goes past him near head height and he does well to evade it.
Full toss timed straight to the cover fielder by Rahane.
On the middle stump this time, Rahane times it well towards leg side where the short mid-wicket fielder does well to make a half stop. No run taken there.
Blocked off his front foot to this short ball.
Guides this shortish ball towards third man to take a run.
Four! Cut away! Short outside off this time. Enough time for Vihari to rock back and cut this through the point region to get his first four.
Poor line! Chase is looking to make the batsman play the ball but is missing his line. Goes way down the leg side, keeper does well to pouch that.
On the pads of Rahane, he flicks it towards square leg and takes an easy double.
On the off side, the batter pushes this one toward cover.
Full and around off, Rahane pushes this straight down the ground past the bowler. The man at mid on is quite straight and cuts it off.
Full and on middle, Rahane pushes this towards mid on.
Outside off, Ajinkya leaves it alone.

FOUR! 100 up for India! Good use of the pace by Rahane here. Length ball outside off, he just opens the face of his bat and guides this one between gully and the slip cordon towards the third man fence.
On the pads of Vihari, he blocks it to short leg.
Wide outside off, Vihari lets it be.
Tossed up on the pads, Rahane pushes this one towards mid on and takes a single.
On the pads, tossed up, Rahane flicks it away towards the leg side.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flat and on off pole, Vihari tucks this one towards square leg and takes a run. Off the mark with this one.

DRINKS! The game looked to be going away from the Windies as KL Rahul and Rahane were cruising along. But just before the break, Rahul gave his wicket away to Roston Chase giving the hosts a way back into the match.
And again. Shortish one outside off, Rahane leaves this for the keeper.
Another shortish one to which Rahane is not bothered.
Shortish outside off this time, Rahane is again aware of his stumps and lets it go.
Covers his off pole to this outside off good length ball, lets it go to the keeper again.
Wide outside off this time, Rahane lets it be.
FOUR! Whipped! Fullish ball on middle for Rahane brings his wrists into play and whips it nicely through the square leg region to get a boundary.
Good length again, worked towards square leg for nothing. Wicket maiden from Chase.
Good length ball on middle, worked off his back foot.
Goes down the leg side, Vihari lets the keeper collect this one.
Dishes out a fuller one to the new man, Vihari who works it towards mid-wicket.
Hanuma Vihari replaces KL Rahul. India needs to rebuild again.

OUT! CAUGHT! Great keeping here by Shai Hope and KL Rahul is out of here in a very disappointing manner. This is bowled flat and down the leg side, Rahul looks to flick it but gets the faintest of touches off his glove on it. The ball goes further down the leg side, Hope follows it and takes a good catch. Rahul is gone and just short of his half ton. Rahul looks very disappointed as he leaves the pitch and he should be as well as this was a nothing ball. The 68-run stand between Rahane and Rahul is broken and the hosts get a much-needed wicket.
Flat and around off, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Spin for the first time in this match. Roston Chase replaces skipper Holder.
Good length ball just outside off, Ajinkya defends it out.
Full and on the fifth stump line, Rahane presents the full face of the bat and blocks this out towards the off side.
Just outside off, Rahane pushes this to the fielder at cover-point.
On middle again, blocked out by AR.
Full and on middle, pushed back to Roach.
Full on middle and leg, Rahane pushes it towards the fielder at mid on.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman, presenting the full face of the bat.

A mild appeal by Holder but nothing given. Going down the leg side to the naked eye and the replays confirm it. Length ball on the pads of Rahul, he looks to flick it but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. The ball rolls towards mid-wicket and the batters take a single. Holder was the only one appealing for this one.
Fullish ball, pushed straight back towards the bowler by Ajinkya.
Outside off, left alone by AR.
Full and around off, pushed towards mid off. No runs taken.
Just outside off, good length ball. Rahane leaves this one alone.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman, presenting the full face of the bat.
Full again, pushed towards the fielder at mid off powerfully.
Played to point off the back foot this time by Rahul.
FOUR! Beauty! Grace! What a shot! Shot of the day for me. Full and wide outside off, Rahul leans into the cover drive and just pierces the gap at cover and the ball this time does cross the fence.

Full again this one on middle and leg, Rahane punches this one down the ground through mid on. Roach bends down to his right and gets a hand to it which stops it from crossing the fence. Three runs taken.
Full on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Change of ends for Roach!
Fullish and on off, defended towards the off side by Rahul.
Length ball on the hips, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Full on off pole, pushed towards the cover fielder.
KL defends it from within the crease this time.
On the off pole this time, Rahul blocks this one out.
Outside off on a good length, Rahul does not fiddle with it.
Skipper Holder back on. 6-4-8-0 for him so far.
Fuller just outside off, Rahane blocks this one towards the fielder at cover.
The hosts have now removed the extra fielders at gully and in the slip cordon and placed them at positions where they can stem the flow of runs more.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Full and on middle and leg, played towards mid-wicket.
Full ball outside off, Rahane powerfully pushes this towards the fielder at mid off.
Length ball, outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Full ball on middle and off, blocked out by AR.
Outside off, Rahul leaves it alone. Maiden over by Roach.
Full and on middle and leg, Rahul pushes this towards the fielder at mid on.
On middle and off, pushed straight back towards the bowler.
The ball strikes the batsman very low on the pads

Lucky here that Rahul has got some bat on it. Full and on middle and leg, Rahul looks to push this towards mid-wicket but gets a thick outside edge and the ball rolls towards the fielder at gully. Had he missed it, he was out plumb in front of the wicket.
Length ball just around off, played towards point off the back foot.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

Slashed and missed. The sucker delivery here by Gabriel knowing that Rahane would be vulnerable and maybe overconfident as he looks to hit this one. Full and wide outside off, Rahane goes for the drive but totally misses the ball. He should be more careful or he might throw his wicket away.

FOUR! Great shot, great punch! Full on middle and leg, Rahane takes one step forward and punches this through mid on for a boundary. Beautiful shot! One boundary in each of the last three overs for India.
Full on middle, pushed back towards the bowler by Rahane.

Good leave by Rahane. Pitching way outside off and moving in, Rahane knows exactly where his stumps are, takes a foot forward towards the pitch of the delivery and then shoulders arms to it. Signs of a set batsman.
Good length ball on the pads, Rahul pushes this towards mid on and takes one.
Again full and on off pole, Rahane blocks this one out.
Fullish around off, pushed back towards Roach.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Great shot by Rahane. Looks like he is getting into the groove here. Full and wide outside off, Rahane pushes it towards the gap at cover and the ball slowly trudges towards the fence. Boundary signalled by the umpire.
On the pads this time, Rahul tucks it between mid-wicket and mid on as he quickly takes a single.
Full and on the off pole, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone by Rahane. Good over for India this, 7 off it.

FOUR! Similar line to the last one, wide and full outside off. This time Rahane punches it in the gap and finds the cover boundary. First boundary after the break. Also, brings up the 50-run stand between KL Rahul and Ajinkya Rahane. A vital partnership here for the Men in Blue.
Full again outside off, the ball goes to the fielder at point on the bounce.
Rahane drives this fuller one down through mid off. The fielder there gives it a chase and the batters take two.
Pushed towards the cover fielder with soft hands by Rahul, he quickly sets off and takes a single.

Nasty! That has hit Rahul in the box. Good length ball just outside off, Rahul looks to block it out towards the off side but gets an inside edge onto it as the ball hits him in the box. He is down and in some pain here.
Shanon Gabriel to partner Roach after Lunch.
Again full and on the off pole, Rahane pushes it back to the bowler. Maiden to start off after Lunch.
Full on middle, played back to Roach off the front foot by Rahane.
Again on middle and leg, Ajinkya plays  this one towards mid-wicket.
On the pads this time, AR blocks this out towards square leg.
Short and wide, Rahane does not go for it and shoulders arms.
First ball after lunch, outside off on a length, Rahane leaves it alone.

We are back after Lunch on Day 1. The Windies players are out on the field and so are the Indian batters, KL Rahul and Ajinkya Rahane. Kemar Roach will continue with the ball for the hosts and will look to break this growing stand. Rahane will face the first ball.

68 runs for 3 wickets in 24 overs. After winning the toss, Holder, the Windies skipper, opted to bowl first. His bowlers didn't disappoint him as they picked up early wickets. And, if the three wickets which fell accounts Indian skipper Virat Kohli and Cheteshwar Pujara among them in single digits, one can understand who was on top early on. However, KL Rahul has looked fluent while Rahane has dug in well to add 43 runs between them. With this strong looking stand, one would feel that both the sides go to Lunch with confidence. When we come back after the break, Windies will look to break this grooming stand while the Indians would want the runs to keep flowing in the second session. We'll be back in a while.
Wide outside off, Rahul leaves it alone. That is LUNCH on Day 1!
Again short of a length outside off, Rahul sways away from this one.
Bouncer this time just outside the off pole, Rahul evades it.
Fullish ball around off, Rahul makes use of the pace on offer and he pushes it in the gap at covers to take an easy couple.
KL chooses to leave this length ball outside his off stump.
Rahul gets on the front foot and pushes this towards cover off the front foot.
Outside off, played towards the gully fielder.

On the pads of Rahul, he flicks it towards square leg and take a couple.

FOUR! Poor effort by Roach in the deep. This is a bit short and outside off, Rahane rocks onto the back foot and pulls it towards deep backward square leg. Roach runs to his left from fine leg, gets a leg to it but is unable from keeping it inside the field as the ball just kisses the fence. Gabriel looks very disappointed by that effort.
Again length ball around off, it pitches and comes back in but not enough. Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Length ball outside off, Rahane does not fend at it.
Full again but this time around middle and off, pushed back towards Gabriel.
Wide outside off, Ajinkya lets it be.

Outside off and full, Rahul pushes this powerfully towards covers but the fielder there makes an outstanding effort as he dives to his left and stops the ball going to the fence. The batters meanwhile take a single.
Gabriel is on for a burst before lunch. He was superb in the first spell. 5-1-19-1 so far.

EDGY FOUR! Rahane being very careful here. This is just a bit short outside off, Rahane looks to block it out towards the off side but gets a thick outside edge on it. It flies away from the slip cordon and towards the third man fence for a boundary.

Full and just outside the off pole, in the slot for Ajinkya but he drives this straight towards the cover fielder.

Good length ball just around off pole, pushed towards the cover fielder off the back foot.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Pouncing on the bad deliveries here, Rahul. Full and just outside off, he drives this one off the front foot through mid off for a boundary.
Rahul blocks this ball back towards the bowler.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Beaten! Good length ball around off, it pitches and straightens. It beats the outside edge of Rahul's bat and leaves him squared up.
Similar line and length, Rahul again does the same thing but this time it only results in a run. 50 up for India with this run. This is the first over from Holder off which runs have been scored.
On the pads of Rahul, he shuffles across the wicket and flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.

Shortish outside off, this time Rahul shoulders arms to it.
Length ball on the hips of Rahane, he flicks it towards mid on and takes a run. His first run after 25 balls. Gritty!
Shortish outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Again full and on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.

Full ball around off, Rahul drives this one beautifully through the covers. The ball is racing towards the fence but is slowed due to the sluggish outfield. The batters take two.
Length ball just outside off, Rahul pushes it towards point off the back foot.
Around the fifth stump line, Rahul again leaves this one alone.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to it.
Outside off, Rahane does not fiddle with it.
Full this time on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Good length ball on the off pole, Rahane looks to block it out but gets an inside edge onto his pads.
Outside off, Rahane does not fend at it.
Full outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder.

Clever bowling here by Holder. Cuts Rahane into half. This time he brings the ball into the batter when Rahane was expecting it to go away. He looks to block it out but the ball goes between his bat and pad to the keeper.
Just outside off, left alone by Rahul. Good over for India, 8 off it.
Similar length on middle, pushed to point again.
Good length ball around off, pushed to point by Rahul.
FOUR! Full this time just around off, a half volley. Rahul gets onto the front foot and pushes this through mid off for a boundary. Rahul oozing class at the moment.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
FOUR! Beautiful shot off the back foot. Good length ball just outside off, Rahul gets on top of the ball and pushes it through covers for a boundary. A treat to the eyes this shot.

Fuller again outside off, pushed again towards covers but straight to the fielder this time.
Full and wide outside off, Rahane pushes this towards cover where the fielder dives to his right and stops the ball.
Wide outside off, left alone by the batter.
Full again on the pads, played towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Outside off, left alone. Good carry to the keeper here as he collects it around his head height.

Length ball just outside off, Rahul defends it out.
