Length ball outside off, pushed to point. Maiden by Holder.
Wide outside off, left alone by Rahane.
Length ball just outside off, Rahane plays this towards gully with soft hands.
Again outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to it.
Fuller and on off, Rahane blocks it towards the off side off the front foot.
Length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Wide outside off this time, Rahul leaves this one.
Good length ball this time, Rahul pushes this towards mid on.
Good shot but equally good fielding on this shortish ball outside off. KL looks to cut but Brooks at point dives to stop.
Good length on middle this time, Rahane works it towards the leg side.
Another good length ball outside off, Rahane pushes this on the off side.
Starts with one outside off ball on the good length. Rahul plays it well off the back foot as the ball rolls towards covers. Rahul takes a run.
Miguel Cummins to start the proceedings after the drinks.

DRINKS! The hosts well and truly on top here as the visitors are 32/3 with Agarwal, KL Rahul and Virat Kohli all back in the hut. Roach and Gabriel bowled brilliantly with the new ball. They didn't offer any freebies and they got dividends for that with three top wickets.
Fullish one to finish the over, Rahane leans forward to block. Maiden over start for the Windies skipper.
Good length ball outside off again, Rahane plays this well again and shouts no run there.
Outside off on a good length, Rahane lets it be as the ball shaped away from him.
Shortish outside off again, Rahane dabs it on the off side again.
Another same line and length ball, Rahane is on his back foot to work it well on the off side.
Shortish one to start with which is outside off, Rahane dabs it towards the off side.
Skipper Jason Holder with the ball now.
FOUR! Nicely done! Gabriel looks to bowl a yorker this time as he dishes a fuller one. KL leans forward and times it superbly and the ball races to the mid off fence.
Good length in the channel outside off this time, KL covers his timbers and lets this go to the keeper.
Shortish ball outside off, this one is left alone.
Shortish one on the middle stump line, The ball rises as KL hops to block it off his foot. There is a short leg but KL dropped it on the pitch.
Short ball on middle, Rahul ducks under it.
Fullish ball on middle, KL flicks it nicely towards mid-wicket to get a couple.
Length ball just outside off, Rahane plays this down towards mid off.
Down the leg side, Rahane tries to flick but misses.

Edged but safe as it flies wide of third slip. Gabriel pitches this on a length outside off and Rahul goes for the cut. He gets a thick outside edge on it but the ball falls safely in the third man region as the batters take one.
That might hurt. Pitched outside off, coming into the batsman as KL looks to play it off the front foot but he is hit on the arms there. Physio out in the middle with the magic spray.
On the stumps on a good length, KL looks to work it towards the leg side but the ball goes off the outer half of the bat to roll towards point.
Good length ball, works it towards mid on.

Hit on the body! Rahane is welcomed with a bumper which hits him on the body. Shortish ball outside off as Rahane prepares to leave it but this comes in with the angle to hit Rahane on the stomach. Top over from Gabriel.
Rahane out in the middle now.

OUT! CAUGHT! Short ball and Kohli is gone. The plan to get the skipper out on the short one has worked here. Gabriel bowls this one just outside off, the ball pitches and shoots off the pitch. The skipper looks to fend at it but is only able to slice it towards gully where Brooks takes an easy catch down to his right. India three down and are in deep trouble here.

FOUR LEG BYES! Shorter again just outside off, the ball sticks on the surface as Kohli looks to pull but misses. It hits him on the arm, pitches just before first slip, spins away and goes between him and the keeper Shai Hope towards the third man fence for a boundary. The first slip dives to his left in an attempt to stop it but does not get a hand to it.
Welcome to the Caribbean, King Kohli! Gabriel bowls a bouncer at 137 kph and near head height. Kohli is barely able to evade it as he just gets his head out of the way in time.
Outside off, Kohli leaves this one alone.

FOUR! Pure class! Kohli showing the genius that he is. This is full and just outside off. Virat just leans into the straight drive and the ball races through mid on towards the fence. Counter-attack from Kohli.
Outside off, Kohli lets it be.
Risky single but he gets through. Kohli survives. Kohli pushes this one towards mid on and sets off for a quick single. The fielder picks it up and has a shy at the keeper's end but Kohli is in.
Full and just outside off, Kohli pushes it back to Roach.
Good length ball just outside off, Rahul pushes it towards cover and takes a quick single.
Outside off on a length, Rahul shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball just outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, Kohli looks to leave this one but the ball comes into him. It hits his thigh pad and the ball rolls towards the keeper.
Length ball outside off, Kohli shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Good shot by Kohli. Fullish and outside off, Kohli gets on the front foot and guides this ball through the gap at point with the outer half of his bat. He gets off the mark with this shot.
Full again on middle and off, played towards mid on.
Full ball just outside off, Rahul gets off the mark as he pushes this one towards covers and takes three off it.
Good length outside off, Rahul lets it be.
The skipper, Virat Kohli walks to the middle with India in trouble here. He needs to continue the momentum from the last ODI.

OUT! CAUGHT! Roach is on fire! What a ripper to get Pujara. Superb delivery outside off, held its line again as Pujara looked to play at it. The ball kisses the outside edge of the bat and Shai Hope is not gonna miss out. The best batsman of the last Test series for India is outta here. He does not look to fiddle at the ball outside off this early in the innings but he felt for that one outside off, maybe because the ball was coming in but left a hint when it came close to the bat. But not the way Pujara starts his innings. What a start for West Indies though.
Fuller on middle this time. This is bread and butter for Pujara as he works it well towards mid on to get a couple. He is off and running.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara blocks it well this time.
Short one to welcome Pujara who looks to duck but is hit on the back.
India's specialist Test batsman, Cheteshwar Pujara is the next man in.

OUT! Caught! Beauty! Agarwal has to depart. Huge appeal from the Windies players as this go past the bat of Agarwal who has again not showed any feet movement. Good length ball from Roach which leaves the batsman just a hint to go past the bat. Holder and Windies appeal in unison but the Umpire is unmoved. That looked close though and Holder goes for the review as he thinks there's an edge. Ultra edge arrives to show a spike as the ball passes the bat. Roach gets a breakthrough for West Indies early on.
REVIEW TIME! Now the Windies seem very confident that it has took the outside edge of Agarwal's bat. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge show that there IS a spike! Agarwal is a goner!
Beaten! Peach from Roach. Shortish ball outside off as Agarwal plays at this one from the crease and is beaten!
Fullish one this time, outside off, KL is not fiddling on this one.
Shortish one outside off again. Leaves this one alone as well.
Shortish outside off again, a bit closer but still not enough to make KL play at that one.
Too wide for KL to reach at that one. It was pitched on the shortish length as well.
Shortish outside off this time, KL dabs it well on the off side.
Good start to the over. Good length ball outside off, KL is not tempted this time as he lets it go to the keeper.
Outside off on fifth stump line as Agarwal shoulders arms. Came into the batsman as it went past the stumps.
Beaten again! That ball held its line. Pitched on the good length ball to beat the outside edge of Agarwal. The ball shaped away after passing the batsman there.
Fullish one on the middle this time, Agarwal flicks it but it goes straight to the short leg fielder.
Fourth stumper this time, Agarwal lets it be.
Beaten! Good comeback as Roach bowls it in the channel outside off, makes the batter play again but this comes back in just a tad bit to get past the edge.

FOUR! Shot! Sweet timing. Fullish ball outside off, Agarwal pushes this through mid off nicely. Brathwaite races the ball to save the four but is beaten. First boundary of the match. The decision was referred upstairs but the fielder was touching the ropes there.

Beauty to end the over! What a ripper that one! Good length ball in the channel outside off, KL Rahul is squared up on this one as the ball comes into the batsman. He is beaten. Lucky to not edge that one.
First runs! Good length ball outside off, Agarwal taps it on the off side and calls for a quick single.
BEATEAN! Good delivery this time. Shortish one from Gabriel on the fourth stump line. Makes Agarwal play who hops to defend but is beaten.
Good length ball outside off again, Mayank plays it well towards gully.
Gets the batsman to play this one as this comes into the batsman from a shortish length, Agarwal blocks it well.
Gabriel starts with one outside off on a slightly shortish length, Mayank lets it go.
Shannon Gabriel to bowl from the other end for the hosts as expected. Gabriel has picked up 25 wickets in the last four Test matches he has played on this venue.
Another one which comes into the batsman, KL plays at it but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Outside off on good length again, Rahul blocks it well.
Another shortish length on off, KL Rahul blocks this onto the pitch with solid defense.
This time a short one, coming into the batsman, Rahul looks to work it through the third man fielder but plays it a bit awkwardly to dab it to the slip cordon.
Gets this to move in from off stump, just a bit from the good length area. Rahul plays across the line to get hit on the pads. A slight appeal but nothing serious.
Roach starts with a shortish ball outside off, KL Rahul lets it go to the keeper. Would look to come closer to the batsman.
We are all set to begin! The Indian openers, KL Rahul and Mayank Agarwal are out in the middle. Kemar Roach to start the proceedings for West Indies. Three slips and a gully in place. Here we go...

Indian skipper, Virat Kohli is happy with how it has panned out. The skipper informs that they want to put runs on the board and put the Windies under pressure. Mayank Agarwal and KL Rahul will be opening the innings for India. Kohli informs about the changes and mentions that Saha, Ashwin, Rohit, Kuldeep and Umesh are left out of the playing XI.

West Indies skipper, Jason Holder, says they are going to field first. Holder informs that his team will bowl first as he feels there is more moisture on the pitch. States the guys are prepared and they are looking forward to face the no. 1 side in Tests. States that they want to start the series well. Informs they are going in with 4 pacers and they have one debutant, Shamarh Brooks.
INDIA (PLAYING XI) - Mayank Agarwal, KL Rahul, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli (C), Ajinkya Rahane, Hanuma Vihari, Rishabh Pant (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Ishant Sharma, Mohammed Shami, Jasprit Bumrah.

WEST INDIES (PLAYING XI) - Kraigg Brathwaite, John Campbell, Shai Hope (WK), Shamarh Brooks, Darren Bravo, Shimron Hetmyer, Roston Chase, Jason Holder (C), Miguel Cummins, Shannon Gabriel, Kemar Roach.
TOSS -  Up goes the coin, Kohli calls heads and it is... tails. The hosts have won the toss and will be bowling first.

Daren Ganga informs that the weather is cloudy here in Antigua. There is a hint of grass on the pitch and it will result in varying bounces. There are dark patches on the pitch due to moisture. Pace will be the dominating factor. Have to bat carefully early on in the innings.  Very good looking pitch but there is more for the seamers than the spinners.
An exciting Test series awaits us in the Caribbean and both the sides will be eager to start their ICC World Test Championship campaigns on a positive note.

The Men In Blue have dominated this tour completely as they have won every match that has been played. A whitewash in the T20 series was followed up by a 2-0 win in the ODI series. The hosts were in a couple of winning situations but failed to capitalize on it. Jason Holder mentioned that they need to take more responsibility in these kind of situations and make the most of them. The visitors need to be on their toes and not take the hosts lightly as they won the last Test series they played at home against the English.

Welcome to our coverage of the first Test of India's tour of West Indies in Antigua. It is the start of both sides' ICC World Test Championship campaign and they will be looking to grab the whole 60 points on offer in this match.
John  Campbell comes into the attack.

India were frustrated in the first half as they were unable to pick up wickets. Now they will look to build up a good lead and bat Windies out of the game. Windies, on the other hand, will look to pick up early wickets and reduce the deficit. Be back in a while for the third innings.

Many Windies batsmen got starts but threw their wickets away at crucial moments. Ishant Sharma was the star for India as he picked a five-fer. Chase was the only batsman who looked like sticking it out  and it is not a good looking scorecard for them.

West Indies have been bowled out for 222 and they trail by 75. West Indies have added 33 runs today and credit goes to Holder for sticking it out and playing a handy innings of 39 runs. Cummins played out 45 balls without scoring a run before Shami got the big wicket of Holder. Jadeja then got the last wicket of Cummins.

OUT! BOWLED! The Windies have been bowled out for 222 and trail India by 75 runs going into the third innings. Cummins is the last man to be dismissed after he faced 45 balls without scoring a single run! Jadeja comes around the wicket and bowls this one flatter and on the off pole, it spins back in just towards Cummins. He goes to slog sweep it but misses the ball altogether and it crashes into the off pole. The stumps are shattered and after a frustrating opening hour for the visitors, they have taken both the wickets quickly after Drinks.
Jadeja around the wicket, bowls this one flatter and on middle and leg, it hits the inside half of Gabriel's bat and the ball rolls towards fine leg for a single.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a good length outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but fails to put ball on it.
Full delivery on middle, Gabriel flicks it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
BEATEN! It is a good length ball outside off, Gabriel looks to drive but misses the ball completely.
Good length delivery on off, Gabriel plays it to mid off.

NOT OUT! BIG SHOUT FOR LBW! Shami bowls a full delivery on the leg stump, Gabriel goes for a flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Shami goes for a huge appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Shami and co. go for a review but it looks desperate. The replays roll in and the Ball Tracker shows that the impact was outside leg stump. Poor review from India and they have lost their first review.
REVIEW TIME AGAIN! This time India take the review but it seems to be going down the leg side to the naked eye and yes, the Ball Tracker has confirmed it. Impact is way outside leg.
Shannon Gabriel is the last man in for the hosts. The skipper is out of here and India will be looking to wrap this up now as soon as possible.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Excellent delivery from Shami. It is a good length ball outside the off stump line, Holder goes for a drive but gets a thick outside edge back to the keeper. The Windies seriously needed Holder to stay out there in the middle in order to get any closer to India's score. A good partnership of 41 runs comes to an end. The hosts still trail by 77 runs.
Again similar delivery, Cummins is beaten again.
Cummins is beaten at this one. Flatter trajectory and going away from Cummins with the angle, he looks to defend but misses.
Holder takes a single and gives the strike to Cummins to negotiate the last 2 balls of this over. Full and pushed towards mid on as Holder crosses end.
Tossed up on off, pushed towards the off side.
This time slower through the air, again defended by Holder.
Flat outside the off pole, blocked out by Jason.
Bouncer! It is bowled on the leg stump line, Cummins does well to duck under it.

NOT OUT! It is a full delivery outside the off stump line, Cummins goes for a defense but misses. Shami and the keeper goes for an appeal and the umpire gives it out. Cummins goes for the review straight away indicating that it has not hit the bat. The replays roll in, the front foot is fine and Ultra Edge shows that there is a distance between the bat and ball. Cummins survives. He has faced 40 deliveries and is yet to get off the mark.
REVIEW TIME! This time the hosts have taken the review and Cummins looks pretty confident that he hasn't edged it. Replays roll in and nothing on the Ultra Edge. Good review by Cummins.
Good length ball on the off stump line, Holder pushes this to cover-point and takes a single.
Good length ball on middel, Holder defends it off the back foot.
Another full delivery on middle, Holder pushes this to short mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Holder flicks it to mid-wicket.

DRINKS! Holder and Cummins have shown tremendous resistance here. Cummins is yet to get off the mark but has managed to stay in there. Holder has looked good and should look to continue inorder to get closer to India's score.
Loopy delivery on middle, Cummins defends it off the front foot back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on middle, Jason pushes this to mid on and gives Cummins to face the last ball of the over.
Floated delivery on middle, Jason defends it to short leg.
Fullish delivery on middle, Holder flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple to keep the strike.
Loopy delivery on middle, Holder blocks it out.
Flighter delivery on off, Holder pushes this towards cover.
This time Shami attacks the stumps, Cummins blocks it out well off the back foot.
Another length ball outside off, Cummins looks to block this one out but bails out in the end.
Outside off, Cummins lets this one through to Pant. Wasteful ball by Shami.
Some pondering by Holder but he trusts Cummins this time and takes a single. Length ball around off, Jason guides it towards the empty point region and takes a single.
Beaten! Holder living dangerously here. Length ball around off pole, it pitches and moves away. Holder hangs his bat at it but the ball whizzes past his outside edge.
Fuller one around off, pushed towards cover by Holder.

Third play and a miss in a row! Cummins has faced 35 balls in this innings and is yet to get off the mark. It is a flighted delivery on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but misses the ball again. He has played and missed a lot of ball in this innings so far and should consider himself lucky to not edge any of that.
Another play and a miss! Cummins attempts to defend this flighted delivery outside off but misses the ball completely.
BEATEN! Another one from Cummins. Jadeja comes around the wicket and pushes this ball outside off, Cummins goes for a defense but misses.
Flighted delivery on middle, Cummins defends it back to the bowler.
Looped up ball on middle, Cummins blocks it out.
Flatter delivery outside the off pole line, Cummins leaves it alone.
FOUR! Boundary to end the first over of Shami today. Length ball outside off, Holder pulls this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length delivery just outside off nipping back in, Holder misses his pull and is hit on the thigh pad.
Fuller this time, pushed towards mid on by Jason.
Again beaten! Outside off, length ball, Holder looks to defend but does so inside the line.

NOT OUT! However, the review has been retained by India. The umpire signaled not out but the ball is clipping the top of middle and leg. This one is pitched on a good length around off, the ball nips back in with the angle and hits Holder on the back pad and carries to Pant after that. Jason is on the front foot and maybe it's his big stature that the umpire takes into account as the Indian players are denied after a loud appeal. After a bit of consideration with Shami, Kohli goes for the review. Ultra Edge comes in and shows no bat involved. Now comes the Ball Tracker, pitched outside off, impact in line, clipping the top of middle and leg. Umpire's call and Holder survives. India though retain the review.
REVIEW TIME! This looks to be hitting middle but Holder is a tall man so you never know. The Indian players think for a while before taking the review.
Full on middle and leg, Holder flicks it to deep fine leg but does not take the single as he wants to keep the strike.
Mohammad Shami comes into the attack.
BEATEN! Another flighted ball outside off, Cummins right now is unable to put bat on it. Miguel goes for a defense again but misses.
Flighted delivery on middle, Cummins finally puts bat on it and defends it to cover.
Flatter delivery ooutside off, Cummins attempts to defend again but is unable to put bat on it.
Another play and a miss! Loopy delivery on off, Cummins goes for another defense and misses the ball.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Cummins goes for the defense but misses.
Full delivery on the pads, Holder flicks it to deep mid-wicket and takes a single.
Spin for the first time in the day. Ravindra Jadeja comes into the attack.
Very full delivery outside the off pole line, Cummins this time leaves it alone.
Another play and a miss! It is another full delivery on the fourth stump line. Cummins looks to defend but fails to put bat on it. It is fifth play and a miss in the span of three overs.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but misses.
BOUNCER! A good one at that. It is aimed at the body and Cummins ducks under it.
Very full delivery outside the off stump line, Cummins leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Holder pushes this to the leg side off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Holder goes for a defense but gets an outside edge which bounces in front of first slip.
NO BALL! It is a low full toss on off, Holder flicks it but does not time it well. It goes past the mid on fielder and they take a couple.
FOUR! Nicely played from Holder. It is a back of a length delivery on off, Holder rocks back and lofts this over the mid on fielder for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle, Jason plays this towards mid on.
Full delivery on off, Holder pushes it to mid off.
On a good length on middle, Holder blocks it out.

Third play and a miss from Cummins! Excellent over comes to an end from Ishant. It is another full delivery outside off, Cummins attempts to defend but gets beaten again. It misses the bat by a whisker.
Another play and miss! It is a full delivery on the fourth stump line, Cummins again goes for a defense but misses it again.
BEATEN! Good ball from Sharma, bowls this on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but is unable to put bat on it. Ishant should look to bowl more on this channel.
Bowls a full delivery coming around the wicket outside the off pole line, Cummins is happy to leave it alone.
On a length outside off, Cummins lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.

FOUR! 200 up for the hosts. This is almost identical to the last boundary. Full and outside off, Jason opens the face of the bat and guides this to the point fence. Cummins now will have to face the first ball of the next over as Holder fails to retain the strike. A very rare expensive over by Bumrah, 9 runs off it.
Wide! Way wide outside the off stump and Holder does not fiddle with it. Wide signaled by the umpire.
FOUR! First boundary of the day for the hosts. Full and around off, Holder just opens the face of the bat and guides it between point and gully towards the third man fence.
Another fuller one outside off, pushed towards the cover fielder again.
Good length ball on off, Holder pushes this to cover.
Fuller on middle and leg, Holder pushes it towards mid on.

Good length ball wide outside off, Holder looks to push it through covers but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball rolls towards third man. There was a run on offer but Holder will keep as much of the strike as he can and that's why he does not take a run.
On a good length outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.
BOUNCER! It is aimed at the body, Cummins does well to duck under it.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Holder pushes this to cover-point and takes a single.

Good length ball on off, Holder looks to defend but gets an outside edge which bounces just in front of Pant. It is another good delivery from Ishant which induces this edge from Holder who plays this with soft hands. The keeper makes a good diving stop on the bounce behind the stumps.
Good length ball on middle, Holder flicks it to fine leg but refuses to take a single.
BEATEN! Good ball from Ishant. It is a good length ball on the fourth stump line, Holder looks to defend but misses. Lucky not to have edged that ball as it just passed the bat by a whisker.
Good length delivery on off, Cummins defends it off the front foot.
Bumrah loses his line here. It is a full delivery way down the leg side, Miguel looks to flick but misses.
On a length outside off, Holder guides it to third man and takes a single. Cummins has two balls to survive.
Good length delivery on off, Holder drives this towards cover and takes a brace. Mayank Agarwal runs after the ball and cleans it up.
Full delivery on middle, Holder drives this nicely towards mid on. No run.
Good length ball on off, Holder defends it off the front foot.
Jasprit Bumrah will continue the attack from the other end. 15-4-36-1 so far from him.
On a length on off, Cummins blocks it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Cummins defends it back to the bowler.
Another full delivery outside off, Cummins looks to defend but changes his mind and lets it go in the end.
BEATEN! Bowls it full on the fourth stump line, Cummins looks to defend but misses it completely.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Cummins leaves it alone.

The physio is out in the middle right after the first ball of today's play. Cummins is hit on the box and he looks pretty shook up one can say. The good news is Cummins is alright and he is ready to continue the battle.
Starts with a good length delivery on middle, Cummins attempts to defend but misses and gets hit on the box. He looks in serious pain here and is lying down on the ground.

We are all set to begin Day 3. The Indian players are in a huddle and take their respective fielding positions. Jason Holder and Miguel Cummins make their way out to the middle. Ishant Sharma will start the proceedings for the day.

Daren Ganga is there for the pitch report. He says that the cracks have opened up and there is rain predicted in the morning session. He is joined by Sunil Gavaskar and he says the pitch has played well but there are cracks which will worry the batters but it should still be good for batting. He further says that the batsmen should not look to drive uppishly on this wicket.

Murali Karthik is down for an Interview with Ishant Sharma. He says that he will look to continue bowling well. He further states that he was not expecting that Windies will come out all guns blazing and after discussions with the skipper, he changed his length to a back of a length delivery where it is difficult to hit the ball. On the commentators suggesting to bowl over the wicket, Ishant says that he is not sure and it depends on the conditions.  Says that he started bowling more fuller deliveries over the last two years which  helped him get more wickets in England and Australia. Sharma states that County cricket has helped him over the last few years.

The wicket of the Windies skipper holds the key for both the sides today because if India get him out early on, the hosts would be in big trouble and the Calypso Kings would want their skipper to take them as close to the visitors total as he can. An enthralling and match-deciding first session awaits us and both the sides will be geared up for it.

Welcome to Day 3 of the first Test match between the West Indies and India. Day 2 ended with the hosts 8 down with just 189 runs on the board. They trail the visitors by 108 runs with skipper Jason Holder and Miguel Cummins on the pitch.
... Day 3, Session 1 ...

Earlier in the day, Jadeja's half ton took India to a above par score. That knock could well prove to be the difference in the end. However, if Holder can do something similar, then we can be in for an exciting day of cricket on Saturday. Do join us at 0930 local (1330 GMT). Until then, its goodbye!

India did not start as well as they would have hoped with the ball but got their lines and lengths right soon after and kept picking wickets at regular intervals. Ishant Sharma was the star as he picked up his 9th five-wicket haul in Tests. Other bowlers supported him well and all except for Vihari, chipped in with a wicket at least.

The hosts started well with the bat but ended up being three down at Tea. After the break, Chase and Hope stitched a good 42-run stand before Chase threw his wicket just before his half century. Hetmyer and Hope continued the good work before a short rain break halted the momentum. The break proved to be a bad one for the Windies as they slipped from 174-5 to 179-8. Now Windies' hopes lie on skipper Holder to get them as close as possible towards India's score.

That is Stumps on Day 2! It has been an absorbing day of Test match cricket with India in a commanding position by the end of it all. West Indies end the Day 108 runs behind the visitors with Holder being the only recognized batsman at the crease.
Slower one this time but closer to off pole, blocked nicely by Holder. And, that's STUMPS on Day 2.
Good length around off again, blocked towards gully by Holder with a solid push.
Fullish around off, Holder lunges forward to block it back to the bowler.
Goes for a slower on this time but it is again wide on the off side, leaves it alone.
Good length outside off, Holder covers his off pole and lets it go to Pant.
Good length ball on middle, rises slightly on the hips, Holder works it fine down the leg side but denies a run.
Jasprit Bumrah comes back into the attack.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Another leading edge as Holder looks to flick this fullish ball towards the leg side. The ball goes to the cover fielder and Holder takes a run. He is farming the strike here.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.

In the air but safe! Good length ball on middle this time, Holder looks to heave this towards mid wicket but the ball takes the leading edge and lobs high in the air. Vihari runs from third man and makes a diving effort but can't reach the ball. Ishant Sharma is not a happy man because of that effort there.
Fuller this time as Holder flicks it nicely towards square leg. He denies the single there.
Goes past the outside edge of the opposition skipper with a beauty. Pitched on a good length closer to the off pole. Holder has a poke at it but misses to put bat on ball.
Shortish length on the hips, worked down the leg side for nothing.
Fullish ball on the pads, Holder flicks it nicely through mid-wicket. They take three before the ball is back to the keeper.
FOUR! Fuller length outside off from Shami. Holder opens the face of the bat and guides this through the vacant third man region to get off the mark with a boundary.
Fuller again outside off, Holder times it straight to mid off.
Full ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler by Holder.
Good length ball on off, blocked by Holder.
Miguel Cummins is the new batsman in.

Another timely wicket for India and another Windies batter walks back after getting a decent start.Ishant gets his third. West Indies still behind by 123 runs.

This time he defends it solidly.

Loopy fullish one this time, pushed back to Jadeja

Nearly a wicket for Vihari! Quicker ball to which Hetmyer looks to push but gets an inside edge which sneaks between bat and pad. Ishant chases it down to the third man to save a boundary. Three taken there.
Shortish one outside off, Hope cuts it through point to pick up a single.
Loopy one Outside off, left alone.

Too straight and flighted one, pushed confidently towards mid on. Hetmyer takes a run.
Fullish one which is pushed back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on middle, worked towards mid off and take a quick run.

The sun is shining now and we are all set to resume. The Indian players go back to their fielding positions after being in a huddle. Out come the Windies batsmen, Hope and Hetmyer.
1648 local (2048 GMT) - Looks like it was just a passing shower as the covers have been taken off with the umpires doing an inspection in the middle. Play should resume soon.

Wow! Another solid timing from Hope. A straight one on a fullish length from Bumrah. Hope gets in the perfect position again and pushes this past the bowler sweetly to pick up another brace.

Timing on that one was superb! Fullish ball outside off, Hope gets into position and plays a perfect cover drive. The ball was racing towards the fence but Agarwal chases  it and save a run as the batters take three.

Fuller on the pads, Hetmyer works it nicely towards mid-wicket to get a single. They wanted a couple there but Jadeja was quick to the ball and they decided against the second run.

OUT! Caught! Sharp catch that by KL Rahul! Chase departs just two short of his half century. Oh wait! The umpires are checking for the no ball there. That looks very close. Well, legal one confirms the umpire and Chase takes the long walk back to the pavilion. This is a good length ball on middle, Chase flicks it off his back foot but KL Rahul at square leg takes a sharp catch. End of a 42-run stand. Timely wicket for India this one.
Starts his new spell with a good length ball outside off, blocked nicely by Chase.
Ishant Sharma comes back into the attack.
length ball on middle, Chase looks to cut but gets an inside edge and the ball goes fine down the leg side. Single taken.

Played off his front foot to this loopy ball around off.

Ishant removed the other opener, Kraigg Brathwaite to pull things in India's court. And then, Jadeja got rid of debutant Shamarh Brooks to leave the Windies in trouble. Back of a length delivery on off, Kraigg blocks it off the back foot.
On a length outside the off stump line, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Brathwite defends this off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, Brathwaite drives this to cover and takes a single.
BOUNCER! A good one at that. It is bowled on the body, Brathwaite does well to duck under it.
Good length ball on middle, Brathwaite flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length on off, blocked well by the batsman.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Just short of the gully fielder there. Superb delivery outside off, Brathwaite fends at it and the ball goes off the outside edge towards the gully fielder but just short of him.
Debutant Shamarh Brooks is the new man in.

OUT! Knocked him over! Shami has a wicket in his first over. Bowled a fuller ball on the fourth stump line to the left-hander. Campbell comes forward to jam the ball but drags it back to the stumps. Campbell was going all guns blazing but this was one shot too many for him.
Fullish one again but on the pads. Campbell looks to flick but misses. Pant does well to stop down the leg side.
Fuller one on the pads, KB tucks it towards min on to take a run.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Beaten outside off this time! Good length ball on off, Brathwaite pokes at it but lucky to not edge.
FOUR! Welcome to the attack, Mr. Shami, says Kraigg. Fullish ball outside off, Brathwaite leans into the drive and times it sweetly through covers to get a boundary.
Shami is on now.
Shortish ball outside off, Campbell leaves it alone.

Short ball on middle, Campbell pulls hard but finds the square leg fielder and takes a single. Jadeja hits the stumps and the ball goes towards cover. The batsmen think of taking an overthrow but decide against it but then the cover fielder throws the ball at the bowler's end thinking of running the batter out but misses. And there's no one to backup the underarm throw and they eventually get the second run. Sloppy stuff this from India.
Good length ball on off, John wanted to leave it at first but changes his at the last moment to defend it.
On a good length outside the off stump line, John lets it be.
IN THE AIR BUT SAFE! Sharma bowls a full delivery outside off, John goes for a drive but does not time it well. However he gets enough to go over the point fielder. The batters take a couple.
Good length delivery on off, John defends it off the back foot towards cover and takes a single.
On a length outside off, Campbell leaves it alone.
Loses his line does Bumrah here, bowls a good length delivery down the leg side, John looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball outside the off pole line, Campbell lets it go.
Bowls a full delivery on the pads, Campbell goes for the flick but gets hit on the pads. There is a muffled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire.
Full delivery on middle, Campbell pushes this to mid on.
Good length ball on middle, John defends it off the back foot.
On a length outside the off stump line, Kraigg leaves it alone.
Inswinger which is bowled down the leg side, Brathwaite looks to flick but misses.
Short ball on the body, Campbell pulls this nicely towards square leg and takes a single.
Good length delivery on off, Campbell defends it to point.
On a length outside the off stump line, John leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, KB flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
BOUNCER! It is bowled way down the leg side, Campbell does not feel the need to play at it and ducks under it.
On a good length on the pads, Campbell looks to flick but gets hit on the pads.

Full delivery on the pads, Brathwaite flicks this nicely towards the square leg region. Ishant Sharma hares at the ball to stop the ball very close to the rope. Good effort that from the Indian pacer. The umpire wants to check if Ishant was touching the rope when he pulled the ball back. Looks a clean stop. Three runs taken.
Good length delivery on the fourth stump line, KB defends it to the off side.
Good length delivery on the off stump line, Brathwaite defends it off the front foot.
Fullish length outside off, left alone by the batsman.
On a good length ball on off, Campbell defends it off the front foot.

FOUR! Excellent batting from Campbell this. Ishant bowls a full delivery outside the off stump, John prods forward and lofts this over the cover fielder for another boundary. Aggressive cricket this from Campbell.
FOUR! It is not a bad ball from Ishant as he bowls this on a length on off, Campbell pushes it through the gully region for a boundary. Campbell is in some mood here.
Inswinger on the pads, Brathwaite flicks this towards fine leg and takes a single.
BEATEN! Good ball from Sharma. It is a good length delivery outside the off stump line swinging away from the batsman. Brathwaite looks to drive but misses.
Good length delivery on middle, KB flicks it but the fielder at short leg makes a good stop.
Shortish one outside off, Campbell taps it towards point.
Good length ball outside off this time, the batter lets it be.
Back of length on middle which comes in to the left-hander. Campbell looks push this off his back foot towards the leg side but gets hit high on the pads.
Good length on middle and leg, the ball seams away. Campbell looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads. Stifled appeal from the bowler but no excitement. It was going down.
Bowls this one on a fuller length but too straight as Brathwaite flicks it towards square leg to get off the mark.
Starts with one on a good length outside off, Brathwaite covers his stumps and leaves it alone.
Jasprit Bumrah to share the attack with Ishant Sharma from the other end.
On a good length ball on off, Campbell looks to defend but gets hit high on the pads.

FOUR! Positive start from Campbell. It is a good length ball outside off, John throws his hands at it and drives this towards the point region for his second boundary. The fielder at point dives to take the catch but does not get a hand on it.
Bowls it too straight again does Sharma, John flicks it towards mid-wicket and take a brace.
FOUR! Good shot. It is a full delivery on the pads from Sharma. Campbell flicks it towards the square leg region for the first boundary of the innings. This will give a lot of confidence to John.
On a good length on middle, Campbell defends it back to the bowler.
LEG BYE! Starts with an inswinger on middle, Brathwaite looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to fine leg and a leg bye is taken

The stars for India were Ajinkya Rahane, Hanuma Vihari and Virat Kohli. Rahane scored his first Test ton after two years which provided a big relief for him. Vihari narrowly missed out on his ton as he was dismissed on 93. Skipper Virat Kohli also scored a half ton. Vihari provided the much needed impetus in the innings as he accelerated the run rate. The West Indies did not have a lot in their locker and Roston Chase was the pick of the bowler's for them as he picked up a 4-fer. Join us in a while to see how the Windies innings unfolds.

The Indians had partnerships all along the way in the second innings. The two big ones especially, one between Rahane and Kohli and the other between  Rahane and Vihari completely took the game away from the hosts. The Windies bowlers looked completely out of sorts and the only bowler who impressed for them was Kemar Roach. Another problem for them was the fitness of the bowlers. Cummins, Gabriel and Roach were struggling throughout the innings as they were repeatedly going back into the dugouts.

So, India have declared their innings after scoring 343/7 in the second innings and they now lead by 418 runs. The Windies will need to beat the world record set by their predecessors if they want to chase this down.

OUT! CAUGHT! No century for Vihari then. And that is a very poor ball to get out to. This is shortish ball going down, Vihari looks to pull this one away but gets a faintest of touch of the gloves and the ball goes down the leg side for Hope to swallow. He does not make a mistake. Kohli declares with that wicket. Target for West Indies will be 419 runs.
Bumper outside off, Vihari is not going to do anything fancy with it. Ducks under it.
Full ball on middle and pads, Jadeja tucks towards mid-wicket and gets Vihari on strike.

FOUR! Vihari going big now as the declaration edges closer. He uppishly plays this one towards mid-wicket by going down on one knee. The ball goes past Holder, from his left at mid-wicket and into the fence.
Floated wide outside off, Vihari drives this towards cover and takes a couple.
Jadeja is the new man in.

Drinks! Lead for India continues to grow with Vihari closing towards his maiden Test ton. Rahane already reached the milestone before getting dismissed. Pant came in and went in the search of quick runs but Kohli doesn't seem to be interested in the declaration at the moment. Interesting hour ahead.

OUT! CAUGHT! Substitute Keemo Paul takes the catch at deep fine leg and Pant's short innings comes to an end. This one was tossed up on the leg pole, Pant gets down on one knee and looks to slog sweep it for a maximum. He does not get proper contact on it as it comes off the toe end of the bat and Keemo Paul does well as he dives forward and takes a difficult catch. India 6 down now and they are looking towards the skipper for the declaration. He says no as he wants Vihari to complete his ton maybe.
Short and flatter this time by Chase, Vihari cuts it towards third man and takes a single.
Very wide outside off, VIhari tries to guide it to third man but misses.
Floated on the leg pole, he nudges it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Roston Chase back into the attack now.
This has been driven superbly to the covers by Vihari.
Full toss on the middle pole and Vihari strikes it back at Holder who grabs it with one hand.

FOUR! This time Vihari mistimes his shot. Bumper on the body, Vihari goes for the pull but top edges it high in the air towards fine leg. Hetmyer hares across to catch that but it falls shot and rolls to the fence.
Goes for a heave over mid off this time but this flies off his outside edge towards backward point. Falls short of the fielder. Pant crosses ends.
Bouncer outside off, Pant looks to upper cut this but plays it awkwardly towards slip.
Fuller one on off, Pant drills it straight to mid off. No runs taken which means he wants to go for the fours and sixes.
Bouncer going down leg. Vihari ducks under it.
Fuller one outside off, Vihari comes across the off side to block.
Bumper on the body, Pant goes for the pull but he is not in a great position. Mistimes the shot which lobs in the air off his gloves and goes to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball around off, tapped towards point for a quick single.
Bumper this time, Vihari ducks under it nicely.
Length ball on the middle and leg, tucked fine for a run.

Edged but dropped! Short ball on the body of Pant who hops a bit to guide it over the slip cordon but can't get the direction it wants. The ball takes outside edge and goes high towards Shai Hope. He plucks his right hand in the air to catch that but can't hold on. The ball rolls behind him and the slip fielder runs to get the ball back. They take one.
Pant is off the mark with a nice cut shot. Short and wide outside off, Pant cuts it nicely through point and takes a quick couple. The lead is 400 now. How much more Kohli and India wants?
Fuller one wide outside off, Pant throws his bat at it finds cover.
Fuller ball on off, punched towards long off for a run.
Vihari comes down the track but misses it completely.
Vihari guides it to third man off the back foot. No runs taken
Next man in for India is Rishabh Pant. Also there is a bowling change as Holder is back into the attack.

OUT! CAUGHT! Signs of urgency? Good length ball on off and middle, Rahane looks to slam this one over cover but mistimes it as the bat turns in his hand and the ball goes off the toe end of his bat towards cover. Holder takes a simple catch running back. Vihari runs towards Rahane to congratulate him. The commentators on air wondered if he was going off with him but that wasn't the case. A brilliant innings by him comes to an end and he is dismissed for 102. He has done well to put India in a dominating position as they lead by 397. The 135-run stand has been broken here.
Bouncer around off! Rahane does well to sway away from this one.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery

NOT OUT! Umpires call and the review is retained by the West Indies. Now this looks very close and indeed it is. Clipping the top of leg pole. This one pitches on middle and leg, and nips back in with angle, Rahane misses his flick and is hit on the thigh pad. The Windies players put in a soft appeal but the umpire denies it. The hosts review as they think it is a close one. Replays roll in, Ultra Edge shows no edge on this one. Hawk Eye comes in and shows that the ball is clipping leg. Nothing going the Windies' way here.
Review time! West Indies have gone for a review after Rahane has been adjudged not out by the umpire. Looked close.
Off the toe end of the bat this one, Rahane looks to smash this full ball outside off over the mid off fielder but does not get enough of the bat on it. Two runs taken as the fielder mops it up.
Length ball on middle and off, pushed towards mid on off the back foot.

When will Kohli think about declaration? Because he is not waiting for the score or target. What he would be thinking is - 'If I declare now and give West Indies 4.5 sessions to play, what if they drain out my bowlers keeping them 100-plus overs in this heat? The second Test is just 3 days away and there will not be time to recover. Better keep batting and declare with an hour to go for the day.'

Beaten! Roach has done this number of times today but has failed to get the outside edge. Another one just outside off, Vihari looks to defend this but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement.
Fuller on the pads, driven towards mid on.
Bouncer this time, around the off pole line. Vihari does well to sway away from it.
Another one just outside off, blocked out by Vihari.
good length one just outside the off pole, the ball hits the splice of his bat and bounces onto the pitch.
Down the leg side, Vihari looks to flick this one but misses as the ball kisses his pads and carries to the keeper. The Windies put in a desperate apppeal but to no avail.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Full toss but can't make the full use of it. Vihari looks to push this towards the leg side but gets a leading edge and ball goes towards cover. They take a run
Blocked off his front foot this time.
SIX! That sailed over. First six of the innings! Shortish ball outside off, too high but Vihari plays this late and helps the ball sail over the third man fence.
Shortish one on the hips, tucked away behind square leg for a couple.
On the pads, flicked firmly by Vihari but straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Shannon Gabriel is on now!

Misfield from the fielder in the deep. Vihari flicks this full ball on his pads towards deep mid-wicket. The fielder from long on runs to his right but is sloppy in picking up the ball. He fumbles and the batters are able to complete the third easily.
Played to the point region by Vihari off the back foot.

100 up for Rahane! Tenth Test ton for him and he has compiled his innings really well after being dropped by Campbell. This one was on the pads, Rahane just pushes this towards mid-wicket and takes a single to get to his 100. The monkey is off his back now and he must be thinking to up the ante from here on. He gives a big hug to the non-striker Vihari and then lifts his bat towards the dressing room as he soaks in the applause.
Full again on the off pole, Rahane pushes it towards mid on.
On the pads of Rahane this time as he shuffles down the track, he flicks it straight to the man at mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, pushed towards the man at point.
Another full one, pushed towards long on for a run.
Fuller on this time, pushed towards mid off for a run.
FOUR! Top shot. Fuller ball on off, Vihari creams his drive wide off Chase and the ball races to the fence in no time. Mid on and long off had no chance
Fuller one on off, jumps out of the crease to push it towards cover for a run.
Flatter, blocked towards the off side.
Loopy ball on middle, punched straight down the ground to pick a couple. 300 up for India with that single.
Beaten! Goes past the hanging bat of Vihari with a superb ball going away from from Vihari. Lucky not to edge there.
Shortish delivery outside off, Rahane guides it through gully and point for a single.
Stays in the crease to this good length ball and blunts it towards point.
Fuller on the pads this time, flicked for a single down to backward square leg.
Good length in the channel outside off, blunts this off his back foot.
Fullish ball on off and middle, Rahane looks to push this towards the leg side but the ball goes off his outside edge towards point for a run.
Kemar Roach to bowl from the other end. He is feeling fine after the Lunch break and will be looking to dent the Indian batting now.
FOUR! Loopy ball on middle and leg, Vihari dances down the track and makes this fuller one into a full toss. He launches this wide off mid on to get a boundary. First boundary of the second session.
Fuller ball on off, pushed towards mid on to take a run.
Flatter outside off, Rahane goes back into the crease to flick this towards mid-wicket. Takes a quick couple.
Flighted on middle and leg, blocked off the front foot by Rahane.
Slightly short and shoots off just a bit off the surface, pushed off the back foot towards point for a run.
Loopy fullish ball on middle from round the wicket, pushed towards mid-wicket.

The umpires walk out to the middle and are followed by the hosts. Rahane and Vihari make their way to the middle as well with the latter taking the strike. Roston Chase will continue the proceedings for the West Indies.
... Day 4, Session 2 ...

The Men In Blue lost skipper Virat Kohli early in the day but his troops continued the good work after his dismissal. Vihari came to the crease and didn't look even a bit out of place and started to score runs at a very good rate as he brought up his half ton in just 77 balls. Rahane played cautiously and is 10 short of completing his tenth Test match ton. The West Indies bowlers have not bowled well and given runs away cheaply. Two of their pacers are in the dugout with some injury issues and the hosts will be hoping that they come back and join them after the Lunch break. Do come back and join us for the second session of Day 4.

LUNCH ON DAY 4! India are CRUISING along! 29 overs, just the 1 wicket and 102 runs in this session. The 100-run stand also came up between Vihari and Rahane off the last ball of this session and the visitors couldn't have asked for much more. They lead by 362 runs.
Full toss on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket for a single. 100-run stand comes up between the two. AND THAT WILL BE LUNCH.
Shorter one, pushed towards point.
FOUR! Loopy fullish ball down the leg side, Vihari sweeps firmly towards the fine leg fence.
Fuller one this time, finds cover.
Shortish one, worked towards the leg side for a run.
Fullish one this time, pushed to covers.
Fullish outside off, pushed to mid off this time.
Flatter outside off, blocked this time.
Jumps out of the crease to drive this fullish ball nicely but can't beat the mid off fielder.
Shortish one around off, blocked off his back foot by Vihari.
Flatter on the body, Rahane goes back to the crease to push towards mid-wicket for a run.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahane blocks out.
Good length ball, angling into the batter, tucked towards the leg side.
Another fullish ball, Vihari punches it straight to bowler this time.
Fuller again around off, Vihari again strokes it straight to the mid off fielder.
Another fuller ball, driven straight to mid off.
Good length ball angling in, worked towards square leg with the angle for a single.
Full on the pads, worked towards mid on, Vihari wanted a run there but is sent back by Rahane.
Blocked off his front foot this time.
Shortish one on middle and leg, pushed towards square leg for a run.
Comes down the track to this wide ball and blocks.
Blocked towards the leg side.
Full one on the stumps, worked with the turn to change ends.
Loopy one on off, pushed through mid on for a run.

FOUR! Top shot to get to his second half century in Tests. Fuller ball on off, Vihari drives it firmly through mid off. No chance for the fielder there. Also, the lead is 350 now. Nothing going Windies' way at the moment.
Shortish ball on the pads, looks to place this down the leg side but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Good length ball coming into the batsman, he pushes this towards cover.
Bumper on the body this time, fended towards point this time.
Good length ball on the body, tucked fine down the leg side to take a couple.
Bumper to start the over, Vihari ducks under it.
Full and floated just outside off, pushed towards mid on for a single.
FOUR! Another boundary. Loopy fullish ball on middle, Vihari crunches it through mid-wicket for another boundary. Top shot that.
FOUR! Length ball but going down, pulled nicely by Vihari. The ball goes to the fine leg fence all along the ground.
Fuller one on off, punched straight to mid off.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, pushed to mid-wicket.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahane comes down the track and pushes this towards mid on for a run. Half stop from the fielder there.
Wide outside off, left alone by Vihari. Maiden by Holder.
This time fuller and outside off, Vihari again leaves this one alone.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
Length ball just outside off, defended towards the man at cover-point.
Length ball outside off, pushed to third man.
Good length ball on middle and off, Vihari blocks it out back to the bowler.
Loopy one on off and middle, pushed through mid on for a run.
Fuller one and wide. Pushed towards off side.
Blocked coming forward to this flatter ball.
Drives this one towards long on to take a run. Sensible from Rahane.

Another flighted ball. Rahane dances down the track to convert it into a full toss and slams this through mid-wicket for a boundary. Poor effort from the long on fielder there as he made almost no attempt to stop the ball.
Loopy full toss on off, pushed straight to the cover fielder.
Short one, closer to off stump, worked through covers for a single off his back foot.
Good length on middle, pushed towards the leg side.
Fuller outside off, blocked nicely by Rahane coming forward.
Fullish one on the pads, tucked towards fine leg for a run.
Bumper but too high. Vihari ducks under it.
Good length ball on off, placed towards point for a run.
Vihari blocks out the last ball off his front foot and into the ground.
Full and floated on middle, flicked towards mid on for a single.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Short again on the body this time, Rahane pulls it towards square leg.
Short of a length outside off, Vihari takes one as he cuts it towards backward point.
Full and floated on middle, Rahane pushes it towards long on and takes one.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fuller one on the pads, stroked straight to mid on.
Shortish one again, pushed towards cover for a run.
Short one around off, tapped towards point.
FOUR! Creamed through the covers. Fullish ball outside off, Rahane leans forward and crunches this through covers
Good length ball on off, blocked nicely.
Jason Holder changes ends.
Full ball on the legs, worked fine for a couple.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Fuller one going down the leg side. Vihar looks to sweep but misses.
Flatter one outside off, left alone.
Loopy one again on off and middle, blocked.
Starts with a fuller loopy ball, Vihari pushes it back to Chase.
Roston Chase is back into the attack. Also we can see Kemar Roach going off the field. Two of the four Windies pacers are in the dugout right now.
Good length ball outside off again, blocked off his front foot.
Good length ball outside off, tucked towards the leg side.
Fuller one this time, Rahane looks to work this through mid-wicket but misses his flick and is hit on the pads. A mild appeal from Windies player but it was going down the leg side.
Good length ball on the stumps again, blocked comfortably by Rahane.
Fuller one on middle, tucked straight to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Wide outside off, left alone.

Poor fielding this time. Good length ball outside off, Vihari directs this through the diving slip fielder with soft hands to take a couple. The fielder gives it a chase and slides to push the ball back in play. Saves a couple.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards cover to take a quick run. Hetmyer there has a shy at the stumps but misses.
Wide outside off, Rahane guides it off his back foot towards third man but Brooks dives to his right to save runs.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Starts with a good length ball which angles in, blocked towards cover by Rahane by getting right behind the line of the ball.
The skipper Jason Holder has brought himself into the attack.
Good length ball coming into the body, blocked off his back foot towards the leg side.
Fuller one outside off, pushed to mid off this time.
Shortish one outside off, Vihari guides it through gully and point to take a couple. The 50-run stand is up with that.
Good length ball on the fifth stump line, left alone.
Fuller ball on off and middle, Vihari blocks it back to the bowler.
Starts with a good length ball around off, blocked nicely.

DRINKS! India still in a dominating position after an hour of play on Day 4. They lost Virat Kohli early in the day but Vihari came in and hasn't looked in trouble. He along with Rahane have scored runs at a very good pace in this hour and have stitched up an unbeaten 49-run stand between them.
Shortish around off this time, blocked on the leg side.

Bumper on the body! Shortish ball coming into Rahane who hops to work this down the leg side but is hit on the body. Rahane looks in pain as the ball has hit him hard. Gabriel struggling too here as he grimaces after bowling the ball. Goes back to finish the over though.
On the pads on a fuller length this time, Rahane works it through mid-wicket for another couple.
Good length ball outside off, rises a bit, Vihari taps it towards point and takes off for a quick run.
In the channel outside off this time, Vihari lets this go to the keeper. Gabriel looks in some discomfort after that ball. However, he goes back to his run-up mark to bowl the next one.
Full ball on the pads, Rahane works it nicely towards deep square leg. The fielder down there cuts it off, so just a run.

Beaten for the third time in the over. Roach looks distraught but gets a clap from his captain. Another one just outside off, Vihari looks to block this one out but again is beaten by the away movement on the ball. A menacing over from Roach comes to an end.
Again beaten! Great bowling by Roach. This time on a driving length, Roach lures Vihari into the shot. He looks to push this one towards mid on but gets beaten all ends up.
Good length ball outside off, Roach is angling the ball into the batsman. Vihari covers his stumps and leaves it.
Beaten! In the corridor of uncertainty this one, on the fourth stump line. Vihari looks to block it out but does so inside the line.
Fuller this time, attacking the off pole here Roach. Vihari flicks this exactly towards the man at mid-wicket.
Outside off, left alone by Vihari.
Good running that. Shortish one coming into Rahane who tucks this one towards mid-wicket and takes a quick couple.
Back of a length around off this time, blocked off his back foot.
Shortish ball into the ribs, Rahane works it fine down the leg side to take a couple.
That made a crunching sound. Fuller one again, Vihari punches it nicely to the left of Roach who made a half stop. The ball rolls towards long on and the batters change end.
Shortish one around off, blocked off his back foot.
FOUR! Sweetly timed. Full toss on off, Vihari drives this nicely wide off the mid on fielder to get back-to-back boundaries off Gabriel. The lead goes over 300 with that boundary.
Fuller again, blocked towards cover.
Good length ball on off, blocked off his front foot.
Fuller one on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR LEG BYES! This one is on middle and leg, Rahane looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the pads. It rolls towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. The Windies players appeal but nothing from the umpire. Ball Tracker comes in and shows to be missing leg. Good that Holder decided against taking the review.
Fuller again, this time on the pads. Rahane flicks this one towards fine leg and takes a couple.
Fuller and just outside off, pushed towards the fielder at cover.
FOUR! Superbly timed! Fullish ball on off, crunched through mid off for a boundary. 7 runs from that over.
Wide outside off, Vihari lets this one go.
Bumper this time, Vihari sways it away.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.
Beaten! Good length ball which came into the batsman with the angle. Vihari looks to cut but he is beaten.
Overpitched ball around off, Vihari leans forward and drives it superbly between cover and point. Paul chases the ball, slides and saves a couple of runs for his side. Good work from the substitute.
Shannon Gabriel comes into the attack for the first time on Day 4 to partner Kemar Roach.
Another ball in the channel outside off, Rahane covers his stumps and lets this go to the keeper.
Good length ball in the channel outside off this time. The ball shapes a bit into Rahane. He blocks by lunging forward.
Another fullish ball on the stumps, blocked nicely again.
Fullish one on the stumps, Rahane works it towards mid-wicket this time.
Good length ball around off again, pushed towards cover this time.
Starts with a good length ball around off, blocked towards the leg side.
Kemar Roach is into the attack now. Also, the West Indies have taken the second new ball at the first opportunity.
Fuller around off, driven straight to Chase.
Blocked by lunging forward this time by Vihari to this full ball.
Fuller one on middle, worked towards the leg side.

Mr. Gavaskar suggests that the hosts should look to bring in the long on fielder in an attempt to create some pressure on Rahane and Vihari. They are taking easy singles and as a result, Vihari is getting the time to adjust himself out in the middle.
Flat and wide, Rahane guides towards third man to take a run.
Flighted on middle this time, worked nicely towards mid-wicket to change ends.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, worked nicely through mid on for an easy single.

FOUR BYES! Goes for the sweep this time as Campbell pushes this down the leg side on a fullish length. Vihari can't get his bat on it while Hope can't do anything else either. The ball races fine for a boundary.
Flighted ball this time, blocked off his back foot.
On the pads this time, tucked fine down the leg side to take a couple.

Welcome to the coverage of Day 4 of the Test match between West Indies and India. The visitors are in a commanding position after three days of play as they have a 260-run lead over the hosts. The Men In Blue have their captain and vice-captain at the crease amidst an unbeaten 104-run stand.

Looking forward to Day 4, India will look to bat the Windies out of the game while the hosts will look to take wickets as quickly as possible. It promises to be an exciting Day of Test cricket. The visitors have not lost any wickets in the first session but Agarwal did survive a scare off the first ball off his innings. That ends the presentation ceremony of the first Test match of the series where the number one side has stamped their authority. They get 60 points with this thumping away win in the ICC World Test Championship. They will go into the second Test with a lot of confidence while the hosts, well they have got a lot of pondering to do. The second Test begins on August 30 at 0930 local (1430 GMT). Till then, take care.

Indian Skipper, Virat Kohli, says that the last time they played here it was outstanding just like today. Praises Rahane and Vihari for their top performance, along with Rahul. Says that as a Test team their temperament is pretty good one. Bishop asks him about how the team is handling Bumrah's work load. Kohli says that Bumrah is the key in the Test Championship and that's why they didn't let him play the white ball series. Kohli also says that they are pretty settled in the pace attack with Yadav and Saini in the ranks. The important thing is sharing the work load. As a part timer Hanuma Vihari does well and can bowl some quick overs and can manage the over rate if needed. Says that Vihari's inclusion was based on team combination and adds that everyone is in the loop during such decisions. On being asked about the role of captaincy, he says it is a responsibility that he is fulfilling and he credits his players for the performances. Says that while he is the leader, the execution is in the hands of the individuals. He expects the hosts to come out hard in Jamaica and will be wanting a professional performance in all departments from his team.

MAN OF THE MATCH, Ajinkya Rahane, says it feels really special as he got a hundred after a long time. He says that the partnership between him and Rahul in the first innings was very important, maybe even more important than the hundred. He dedicates the century to the people who backed him throughout this tough phase. Informs that the wicket was pretty damp on the first day and the Windies bowled very well early on. The plan was always about batting on and the runs would automatically come.

West Indies skipper, Jason Holder praises his bowlers but wants his top order to be consistent. He says that they are leaving too much for the middle order. He further states that they needed to bat better in the first innings. On his team selection, Holder states that they played with the same combination in their last series against England and played really well. Says that they have themselves to blame for this poor performance. Further goes on to say that the Indians bowled really well and spells like these can dismantle any batting lineup. Hopes to turn things around in the second Test.

Jasprit Bumrah, the man who got a fifer in the second innings is giving an interview to Murali Kartik. He says that he is feeling good about the win. Says that he along with Ishant were using the wind to shape in and shape away the ball respectively. On being asked by Kartik about his action, Bumrah says that a lot of hard work goes into developing the action, hiding the variations and deceiving the batters. He adds that playing regular Test cricket has helped him a lot. On being asked about the wicket, Jasprit says it was on the flatter side. Kartik asks Bumrah about what the conversations are between the trio of fast bowlers (Him, Shami and Ishant) Bumrah responds that they communicate a lot between them. They suggest each other just to bowl in the good areas even if they are not getting wickets. On being asked some competition with himself after a bit of disappointment in the first innings, Bumrah says it was nothing as such. He was feeling a little sore in the back after returning from the break. Murali thanks him jokingly about earning everyone a one day break.

The Indians extended their domination with a superb batting performance in the second innings with Rahane raking up a ton after a long time. He stitched important stands with skipper Kohli and then Hanuma Vihari. Kohli fell after reaching his half century while Vihari got out pretty close to his maiden ton. The Windies bowlers apart from Roach never looked threatening in the entire second innings.

For Windies, during their first innings, almost all the batters got a start but could not convert them into a big one. Ishant Sharma was the star for the Indians in the bowling department as he picked up a fifer, helping India take a 75-run lead.

Going back to the first day, the Windies started strongly by taking three quick wickets . But KL Rahul and Rahane got the visitors back in the game with a good stand. Rahane along with Jadeja got to their half centuries and made sure the Indians had a decent total on the board. The Windies bowlers, on the other hand, were ordinary after making early inroads due to which the Windies fell behind in the game.

Bumrah and Ishant started thumping the hosts early on with  wickets at regular intervals. The hosts never recovered after that and had no answers to those unplayable deliveries. Shami came in and did his bit to dismiss the two Windies batters in a single over. Jadeja got some stick from Roach in his 4-over spell but that just delayed the inevitable as Ishant finished the innings with a bumper.

Sensational stuff from the Indian bowlers to bundle the hosts for their lowest score against India in Tests. First win in the ICC Test Championship campaign for India with this one. Indians were always the favourites to win this match but they were absolutely lethal in doing it.
