On the pads, floated by Jadeja. Chase blocks it out.
Short and wide outside off, Chase cuts it off the back foot and takes a couple.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.

NOT OUT! Yes! Going down. Good decision from the umpire. Bumrah bowls a beauty. This one has swung in and hit Roach on the knee roll as he misses his block. It seemed going down the leg pole and the Hawk Eye confirms the umpires decision.
Review time! Huge appeal for the LBW! Given not out by the umpire. Kohli goes for the review. That looked going down the leg side.
Outside off, left alone by Roach.
The ball strikes the batsman very low on the pads
Roach is the new man.

OUT! 5-fer for Bumrah and the Windies skipper is out of here as well. India three wickets away from a victory here. Trademark Bumrah delivery as he bowls a yorker on the off pole, Holder plays down the wrong line as the ball shapes a tad bit away past the defense of Holder and shatters the stumps behind. Fourth fifer for the pacer in Test matches.
Length ball around middle and off, blocked out by Holder off the back foot.
15 overs, 37 for 6. Can India finish this today itself?
Full and floated outside off, pushed through cover by Holder for three. He retains strike.
FOUR! This is way too short and Holder dispatches it. He rocks onto the back foot and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Fuller and floated, blocked out by Holder.
Another one flat and on middle, pushed back towards Jadeja.
Outside off this time, pushed to point.
Flat and around off, the ball pitches and turns away sharply. Holder looks to block this one but is beaten.
Spin time as Jadeja is on!
Fuller length again to finish the over. Blocked nicely again by Bumrah.
Another fullish one which Bumrah wants to hit the target with. Chase is right behind the line again. Blocks well.
Fuller one again on a good length. Chase gets behind the line of the delivery to block towards the leg side.
Another good ball. Good length, angled away this time. Left alone by Chase.
Another fullish ball but this is on the leg side. Holder goes for a flick but misses to get hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and the batters take a bye.
Bumrah wants to shatter the timbers as he bowls another fullish ball which comes into the right-hander. Holder plays late and does well to block.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.

DROPPED! Second drop of the innings and this time it is Holder who survives. On the hips of Jason, he flicks this one uppishly towards the square leg where Vihari was stationed. The last one fell short but this one carried to him at the perfect height to his right. Vihari gets two hands to it but it wobbles out. Ishant looks disappointed with him but captain Kohli tells him to keep his chin up.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Another one outside off, left alone by Holder.
On the pads this one, flicked by Holder and this is just short of the square leg fielder. Almost carried to the fielder this one.
Outside off, left alone by Holder.
Beaten again! Good length ball closer to off pole, Chase has a poke at it but the ball shapes away to get past the outside edge.
Length ball which comes in this time. Holder goes to flick this but is hit on the thigh pad. There is an appeal from the Indians but nothing from the umpire. This was going down the leg side.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.
Goes past the outside edge this time. He continues to swing the ball away from the right-handers from a good length area. Holder has a poke but is beaten.

Fuller outside off this time, Holder looked to drive but withdrew his decision at the last moment. Gets hit low on the bat and the ball goes towards the slip cordon. There is a direct hit at the striker's end but he is safe.
Skipper Holder is the new man in.

OUT! BOWLED! Hope is outta here! The off pole is sent cartwheeling by Bumrah again. His fourth wicket of the innings and he looks imperious with the ball in his hand right now. This was a good length ball around middle and off, it swings away after pitching. Hope tries to block it out but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement of the ball. It crashes into the off pole and the Indian players are ecstatic as the Windies are 6 down. Almost an unplayable delivery this and the visitors are just four wickets away from a victory.
Sloppy fielding which allows a single. Good length ball on off, Hope pushes it towards mid off.
Good length ball is been pushed towards cover.

HUGE APPEAL FOR A CAUGHT BEHIND! Not out says that umpire. This is a peach from Ishant which pitches on a good length ball and comes in. Hope looks to work it down the leg side but is late in the shot. Pant pouches the ball behind and makes a huge appeal. He looked confident but Kohli does not go for the review. A good call from the Indian skipper as the Hawk Eye suggested that it hit the back pad of Hope and not the bat.
Good length ball on off, this time Hope blocks it off his back foot.
Fifth stump ball on a good length, left alone.
Beaten! Superb ball from Ishant. Good length ball which landed on the fifth stump line and came closer to Hope. He has a poke but is beaten.
Fuller one to end the over. Chase lunges forward to keep it out.
Length ball closer to the off pole, blocked off his front foot.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fullish ball this time from Bumrah. Chase misses his flick and is hit flush on the pads. Appeal from slip cordon but nothing from Bumrah as he knew this was going down the leg side.
In the channel outside off, Chase covers his off stump and lets it be. The ball came in as it went past the stumps.
Good ball that but played nicely too. Came in with the angle from a good length. Hope pushes it towards mid-wicket and takes a run. He is off and running.
FOUR LEG BYES! Inswinging ball on the pads, Chase goes for another flick but misses to get bat on ball. It hits the pad and goes fine down the leg side for a boundary.
Bumper but too high. Chase sways away from it.
Good length ball outside off, Chase directs it through gully and point to pick up a couple. Good batting from Chase.
Fullish on the fourth stump line, Chase blunts this towards the off side.
Wide outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Off the mark with a superb shot. Fuller ball on the pads for Chase who flicks it nicely through backward square leg for a boundary.
Ishant to bowl from the other end.
Good length again but shapes a bit away. Left alone by Hope again.
Another good length ball in the channel outside off, Hope lets its be.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.

The Indians are out on the field in the huddle. They disperse and take their positions following the pep talk by the skipper. Roston Chase and Shai Hope are out in the middle. The latter will be on strike. Jasprit Bumrah to continue his over.
... Day 4, Session 3 ...

The second session started with the Indians scoring runs at a very good pace. Rahane and Vihari led India to a huge target of 419 runs. It was a daunting task for the West Indies and they did not live up to it. The visitors came out to bowl with just one intention, 'ATTACK', and so they did as they have dismantled the West Indies batting order with half the side back in the hut with just 15 runs on the board. The victory is almost inevitable now as the Indians will be looking to end this match today itself and seal the victory. Join us for the third session as it might as well prove to be the last one of the match.

DOMINATION! Utter domination by the Indians and they look to be in a hurry to finish off this match. They have taken 5 wickets in 7.3 overs of the second West Indian innings and put themselves on the brink of their first victory of the ICC World Test Championship campaign.

OUT! BOWLED! Bumrah is on fire! Number three for him and half the Windies side is done inside 8 overs for just 15 runs. Fuller ball on off, swinging into the batsman. Bravo looks for a drive by being rooted in the crease. The ball swings in to sneak through the bat and pad to shatter the stumps. Bravo has no clue what happened as he walks back to the pavilion. AND THAT WILL BE TEA ON DAY 4.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Fuller one on the pads, Bravo goes for a flick but this goes uppishly over short backward square leg. The ball rolls fine and they take two. Off the mark with that.
Chase is the new man in for Windies.

OUT! CAUGHT! This time Hetmyer holes out and Rahane makes amends for the dropped catch by his skipper. Fullish ball outside off, Hetmyer looks to drive at this one but he was nowhere near it. The ball moves away after pitching, it gets the thick outside edge of Hetmyer's bat and this time Rahane at third slip makes no mistake. Hetmyer, unlike Rahane cannot make the most of the dropped chance. West Indies 4 down and their wickets are falling like ninepins.
NO BALL! Good length ball on middle and off, blocked out by Hetmyer.
On the pads this time by Ishant, Bravo tries to flick but misses and the ball kisses his pads. It was rolling down towards fine leg but Pant does well to dive to his right and stop it.
Length ball on the off pole, pushed back towards the bowler by Bravo.
Length ball outside off by Ishant, Bravo lets it be.
Good length ball outside off, Bravo covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish ball in the channel, Bravo drops his wrists and allows the ball to the keeper.
Outside off, left alone by Hetmyer.
Another one outside off, Shimron lets it through.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.

DROPPED! An unlikely one by the skipper here. Another one around off on a length, Hetmyer defends at this one and gets an outside edge on it. It carries straight to Kohli at third slip but he puts it down. KL Rahul tries to go for from second slip but is too late. India would have put themselves in a strong position to wrap up this match today itself had the skipper taken this.

Beaten! Bumrah getting some great movement here. This is pitched around middle and off, Hetmyer looks to defend but does so inside the line. The ball whizzes past the outside edge after it pitches and straightens. Oohs and aahs by the Indian players.
Length ball around middle and off, pushed towards mid off by Hetmyer.
Bumper but too high as Bravo ducks under it. Pant leaps high in the air and gets his hand to it. Saves runs.
Shortish ball on the hip, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Good length ball, tapped to point.
Beaten the outside edge! Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer pokes at it but the ball goes away a tad bit.
Good length ball outside off, shapes a bit away from the left-hander. Left alone.
Hetmyer is the new man in.

OUT! LBW! Another one! Game over on the fourth day? Full ball on middle from Ishant, Brooks looks to flick this but misses it altogether to get hit flush on the pads. Huge appeal follows and the umpire raises his finger after thinking. The batters converge to discuss about taking a review but they decide against it. A good call eventually as the Ball Tracker arrives and it shows that the on-field call would've stayed as the ball was clipping the leg pole.
Good length ball down the leg side, Bravo looks to flick but misses to get hit on the pads.
Darren Bravo is the new man in for Windies.

OUT! BOWLED! Knocked him over with a ripper! Fullish ball on off, Campbell is rooted to his crease as he goes for an expansive drive but misses the ball altogether as he played down the wrong line. The ball sneaks in to uproot the off stump. Windies in all sorts of trouble early on.
Fullish one wide outside off, left alone.
Fullish one outside off, driven wide off cover for a quick single.
Shortish one on the body, tucked to square leg for a run.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket to take a run. He is off the mark with that.
Good length ball in the channel, pushed towards gully.
Fullish ball closer to the stumps, blocked off his front foot.
Good length on the stumps, blocked coming forward this time.
Good length ball outside off, Campbell looks to defend but is beaten as the ball shapes away.
Good length ball outside off, left alone again by the left-hander.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on off, blocked off his back foot.
Good length ball outside off, goes further away as Brooks lets it go.
The next man in for the hosts is Shamarh Brooks. West Indies in trouble early on in the chase.

OUT! First blood drawn! Exactly the kind of start India wanted. Good length ball outside off which shapes just a tad bit away. Brathwaite fends at it but gets an outside edge on it and the ball goes straight to Rishabh Pant behind the stumps. Brathwaite's poor run in the game continues but he would have wanted to continue here as West Indies are way behind India. The Windies lose their first wicket and they still need 412 runs.
Good length ball closer to the off stump line, pushed towards cover for a quick single.
Shortish ball outside off, left alone by the batsman. The ball shaped in after passing the batsman.
Shortish ball on the body, tapped onto the pitch by Campbell.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped towards point for a single.

Fuller one outside off, Campbell goes to drive but ball goes off his outside edge towards the second slip who dives to his left to stop that. He picks the ball up and has a shy at the bowler's end which hits. There is a run out appeal out of nowhere which has been taken to the TV umpire. However, Kohli was heard saying that Brathwaite's bat never went out of the crease as per Murali Kartik on air. The batsman is safe as he plonked his bat in. Risky but Kraigg survives.
FOUR! Shortish ball outside off, Campbell goes back and guides this towards third man to get his first boundary.
Length ball outside off , KB goes to cut but this goes off his inside edge and goes fine down the leg side. A single taken. First run for Windies.
Good length ball outside off, Brathwaite pushes this towards the off side.
Starts with a fullish ball down the leg side. There is a leg slip positioned and that's why that delivery. Brathwaite misses his flick.
